{"id": "1099", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "A collector contacting a consumer via email, voice mail, or text message should identify themselves and say what they are calling about (e.g. overdue ABC account) without details of amount, account #, etc.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "So what if a third party might possibly conclude this person has debt?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Without details they still don't know anything.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I personally never return any calls about \"an important business matter\":", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "if you don't tell me who you are or what you are calling about, I consider it spam.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "If you call in good faith to clear up an outstanding balance for ABC company, then you should say so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It's the ones that are trying to scam consumers that give as little detail as possible in hope that someone panics and fills in the blanks for them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1239", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have not heard of anyone in the US being imprisoned for their debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been in the business for 20 years ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and rest assured, while there are 'debt buyers', the majority of agencies are contingency based collections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1414", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would disagree that there is confusion among consumers about SOL which would, as you suggest, require the need for a national SOL.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "The only time I have personally seen SOL straddle a line is when a consumer moves to another state with a different SOL.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The clarity needs to be in these such cases.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Because once a debtor moves, both parties claim the SOL where it benefits them for their desired outcome.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "A national SOL only benefits the debt collectors and not the consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "The focus should remain on creating, as best as possible, a win-win solution that benefits the debt collectors the consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Having a national SOL of 7 years as ACA International wants compromises state laws wherein some states of SOL of 3 years (and otherwise less than 7).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "A SOL is meant to bring resolve.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "And in reality, if a debt collector/debt owner can not resolve their clients issues within the already established SOL of each state, then extending the SOL or having a national SOL under which to bring suit does nothing but allow debt collectors to continue to harass consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Three years really is more than enough time to sue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "Just as criminal defendants are entitled to a quick and speedy trail, so should consumers who may/may not be aware they have an outstanding debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "That is to say: having a national SOL is a guise to prolong resolution rather than a more quick a final resolve in when to bring suit.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "835", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Work email can be handled in a foti-compliant manner, where the email body doesn't disclose the debt but includes content in a link, that is part of the email but isn't available for viewing by the administrator.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Social media and text messages can be handled the same way.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "829", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't really care if manual dialing costs you more money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "You obviously have never been subjected to dozens of misdirected robo calls from debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "797", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is unreal.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Reading your \"if there is a new federal rule regarding messages...\" It seems like this agency is trying very hard to make it easy to get around the court decision which is one of the few that protected consumers,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and they also seem to try to protect the company that abuse the phone because what these people do is harassment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They know it,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and they know how to do it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "They've gotten away with it for so long", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "because they answer to no one,", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "you've put the onus on the consumer to have to sue a debt collector who violates the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "This is unreal.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "203", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "There is currently dispute among federal district and circuit courts as to whether a post-default assignee of a debt comes within the creditor exception.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should issue a rule providing that a post-default assignee is a collector for FDCPA purposes.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "302", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I would suggest a review of the language already published in the Federal Rules of Bankruptcy BR 3001( effective date 12/1/2012) relating to documentation.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Based upon my participation with the Rule and numerous comments/hearings, I believe some time can be eliminated without re-inventing a different set of standards.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Bankruptcy involves collection and involves consumers including attorneys on both sides as well.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "I recommend another examination of the \"validation\" notice language and the litany of interpretations of the language.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "207", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I work at a private university", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and we do not sue for collections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Since the debt can be reported to the credit bureau for 7 years,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "we like to keep our accounts at collection agencies during that entire time.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "With the language now being offered due to time-barred states, our collection agencies do not want any of our accounts older than 4 years (TX).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "788", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "The letter I received just said this communication is for the purpose of collecting a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "First, it was supposed to be a \"validation\" letter,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "but they don't bother to validate", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "they jump the gun.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Communication is always the best way to avoid confusion,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "so I don't think it would be a hardship on anyone to state clearly this is a debt collection agency/company", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "why use euphemisms.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "And then to state unless such and such is paid by (whatever time frame is legal) this will be placed in collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I believe there is some rule now to that effect,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "what I think the problem is, it is not handled consistently.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Each of these many many debt collectors do their own thing.", "reasons": ["11_12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Some are better at communicating than others.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Some deliberately do NOT communicate, for deliberate reasons.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "policy", "text": "Crafting consistent rules and regulations should be the start.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "And then actually requiring these companies follow them.", "reasons": ["15"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "If you don't put teeth into it, none of these collection agencies will bother.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "fact", "text": "There are already rules.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "But we are here because of lack of obeying the law, lack of ethics, lack of clarity in the law, and in my opinion, laws that are slanted against the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "220", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Assuming debtors have a valid address, which is some cases they do not, ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "additional notice that the debt is being assigned to a third party collection entity is no benefit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "My experience is intervention to collect by a third party normally occurs when the consumer is over 180 contractual delinquent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Furthermore, if the consumer receives the warning the account would be placed with a third party", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Many and more confusing to the consumer and agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1344", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, the Massachusetts model sounds very sensible", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "and the Feds should consider adopting it or something similar.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Two contacts in a 7-day period is plenty,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but I think wherever the limits are set they will have to be very strictly enforced.", "reasons": ["4", "6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "These collectors will find any loopholes, excuses or reasons to get around a regulation like this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "There has to be zero tolerance, every time, no exceptions.", "reasons": ["4", "6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "They have violated our privacy and the right to peaceful enjoyment of our home one too many times.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "665", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, I am also concerned with whether or not collectors should identify themselves in a message, or if they should be more general in identifying who they are in a voice message as to not invade the privacy of the debtor for whomever else may share the same answering machine or otherwise may over hear the message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "So far, I have purposely remained neutral on this matter", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "because I have yet to form an opinion.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I can see both sides of the arguments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I think I lean more to wanting the collectors to be more discrete and general about who is calling,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "but I still am not sure.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The big concern that is more concrete is definitely the phone number caller id,", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "in that it should be the true number of the business and (if a message is left) should also be the call back number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1207", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have not encountered a situation in which the bill collector is hired by a business for many decades now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Usually the debt collector has bought the debt, usually for pennies on the dollar, from the original creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I also disagree that the law provides a way for consumers to steal from businesses.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If anything, I would say we have become in danger of reverting to the tyranny of Dickens' time, where a person and that person's family, including children, would be imprisoned for debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Surely we can agree on reasonableness when it comes to how we treat each other, whether debtor or creditor?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "326", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "banks can simply add this provision to their Loan Sale Agreements.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "All buyers executing a Loan Sale Agreement containing such a provision would be contractually obligated to refrain from litigating or threatening litigation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "some current buyer would refuse to purchase with such a provision", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and other current buyers would expect a price discount", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "because they woudl not be able to sue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "In both instances, any inventory not acquired by current buyers would be quicly snapped up by other purchasors who would be willing to comply with these contractual provisions.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Such a resolution would obviate the necessity of legislation or regulation", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "as the matter woudl have been taken care of under the contract between a willing seller and a willing buyer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "there would be no constitutional question regarding the restricting of law suits ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "nor would there be any delay in implementation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "All that would be required is the cooperation of the selling banks", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "which could be induced readily with some Safe-Harbor language for banks that follow this protocol.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "350", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "A notice should go out that the debt has been sold", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "because it definitely informs the consumer in how they should go about negotiating repayment of the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "When the debt is sold, it is sold for significantly less than what is owed,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and the lender gets to write it off,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "and the borrower takes a 7-year negative hit in their credit profile.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Sometimes when you are dealing with debt collectors, the \"debt collector\" is often a wholly-owned subsidiary of the \"original\" lender, which means they get a tax write-off; you get a hit in your credit; and they still try to collect on the entire amount.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "If a debt is sold, then it should actually be sold to a third-party, and not a subsidiary of the original lender.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "And consumers should get full disclosure on who their debt has been \"sold\" to.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "404", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am concerned about the perception consumers have concerning older debts.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "With the knowledge that this legislation is both to improve debt collection practices (helping the credit industry) and to educate and protect consumers (to increase confidence and enforce their rights), this is especially relevent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Many consumers appear to be under the impression, if they haven't managed to pay off the debt within the first initial years, they should *ignore* it until it falls off their credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Reviving the debt is the issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Yet these consumers are not concerned about paying the debt off in full", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "they might be in much better financial standing now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "They're concerned about how paying a debt affects their credit score.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I believe this should be concerning.", "reasons": ["8", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "If a debt is outstanding, and repying part (or all) of this debt actually would *worsen* a consumer's credit, it seems counter-intuitive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It works both against the interests of creditors and debt collectors - and the interest of consumers who owe money on a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I don't know of a viable solution,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "but I'm certain this is a concern which should be addressed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "826", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I bet YOU never had your phone number programmed into a robo-dialer?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I can assure you that it's lots of fun.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Costs too much to do manual dialing?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Too bad.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "748", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Patience is the number one option.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Agree to contact the credit card company and have the debt reduced to what it was at the time of default.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Agree to even a 5 dollar monthly autopay with the promise that eventually it will be increased.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Then report the account in good standing to the credit bureaus as long as those five dollar payments come in.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1053", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "My client needs to see a particular doctor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "When she called his office she was informed that she needed to pay on her account of $278.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "She was not even aware that she had a balance there", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "she had never received a bill from this office ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and when she asked when this bill was from, the gal told her 1986.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "They claim they never turned it over to a collection agency ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "but the client filed bankruptcy in 2005.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "It is listed in her bankruptcy ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "but the doctors office won't forgive the bill.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "If a debt owners want to collect on debts they need to send out bills ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "so families know they have bills due, ", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "that only makes sense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "My client is disputing the bill, but with no luck so far.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "412", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If surviving spouses signed or agreed to a contract or extension of credit then they are obligated to repay in my opinion.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Also, certain states that have community property laws may require a spouse to repay a debt even though they did not sign the contract.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I believe the executor or administrator should investigate whether any debt was disputed or possibly fraud.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "To start they should obtain a credit report for starters regardless whether collectors disclose either way.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "If a collector knows a service member passed away, then the spouse, executor, administrator should not be contacted and the account closed law or no law", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "as I have seen this type of issue arise over the years and have seen and approved accounts closed in the event a service member passed away.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "344", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a monetary \"floor\" required before debt collectors can pursue uncollected debts in court.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The idea that corporations that already charge puninshing interest rates and fees can clog the court systems trying to collect a few hundred bucks from someone who is unemployed, ill, or otherwise unable to pay is counter-productive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a minimum amount of consumer debt owed before creditors can sue debtors.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Another issue with using state and local courts to settle debt collection suits is that it burdens jurisdictions already heavily burdened with cases and strapped for cash.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "236", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If the present mortgage repayment debacle is any indication of noticing or added noticing I think it is much simpler to notify the consumer whom to pay and list the original creditor name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Also, I think it would be a good idea for CFPB and the industry to combine this with FCRA issues.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "For example, if a consumer today reviews their credit reports the normal term is \"sold to another lender\" but no name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have heard similar stories from attorneys who try to match what a consumer lists as a creditor versus what is listed in a credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Seems to me that everyone is trying to close the back door but leaving the front door open.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1049", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe the most significant problem is due to financial institutions having two systems that are not fully integrated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "One is the system of record that contains account level information ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and the second is a charge off system that is used to track events that occur after the account is charged off.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Events that occur on the charge off system are normally not reported to the system of record.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Also, charged off system does not or is not used for credit reporting.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The second problem is a result of mergers and/or acquisitions where the financial institution only converts the system of record and not the acquired charge off system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This leaves a void as to the particular status after the account was charged off.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "As accounts are outsourced or purchased ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "the reliance of information resides on the system of record and NOT the charge off system.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "The third problem involves a consumer who has more than one account with the original lender so the risk of one account going to a different agency or debt buyer is highly likely.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "Even if access by the debt buyer and collector is available, the events that took place on the account are normally not recorded in the system of record and the charge off system may have been decommissioned.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "As to the issue of credit reporting of disputes depends upon whether an agency or debt buyer furnish data to a credit reporting agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "The amount of consumer data currently and in the past reported to credit reporting agencies may not be accurate specific to charged off accounts", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "and to require a chain of title would be expensive ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "and the likely hood of accuracy would still not be achieved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "policy", "text": "Going forward I think the first focus must be on credit reporting accuracy.", "reasons": ["12_14"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "966", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As I have had many accounts in collection due to an identity theft, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have several different experiences with the \"validation\" process.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "My belief is that there is no rule defining exactly what documentation constitutes validation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "As we know, if we dispute with the CRA and ask for a reinvestigation, all that will be done is the social security number will be matched and verified with the amount owed. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It is a useless tool and a waste of the consumer's time.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Asking for validation with a collection agency is almost as useless.", "reasons": ["6", "7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "This is because current laws suggest that the collection agency provide the consumer with information \"such as\" the name and address of the original creditor, and the amount owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "This does not prove a debt is still owed, and to whom it is owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "If we are going to allow companies to buy debts for amounts as low as pennies on the dollar, then the burden of proof MUST lie with the collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "As they are in the business of collecting debts,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "they are given all information regarding payment history, original contracts, methods of prior payment, and all personal information relating to the consumer.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "For far too long the consumer has been at the mercy of the collection agency.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "We are forced to send proof of our identity, current mailing address, phone number, etc. as well as all documentation we have regarding the account that would show an error has been made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "fact", "text": "The collection agency has this information readily available.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "And if they do not, the account should be permanently deleted.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "policy", "text": "If the collection agency cannot produce documentation from the original creditor including (1)a contract (2)payment history from original creditor if any (3)proper identification of the consumer (4)proof of purchase of the debt (5)proof they are legally able to collect on the debt in the consumer's state-then there should be laws in place that prevent the debt from being reported.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "fact", "text": "In most cases, it is being reported from the original creditor already.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "policy", "text": "And if it isn't, this should be a red flag to CRA's that the debt is not valid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection agencies must be able to show proof that a collection notice was sent,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "policy", "text": "and they should be required to provide the same proof a consumer must provide to prove a dispute was sent (CMRR).", "reasons": ["20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "policy", "text": "If it is required of the consumer, it should be required of all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "policy", "text": "A debt should be considered validated only when all of these conditions have been met.", "reasons": ["22"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "value", "text": "Without these safeguards, a consumer could end up paying a debt they do not owe.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "value", "text": "It happens all the time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "value", "text": "How many stories have you heard of collection agencies voluntarily providing any information to a consumer before demanding money?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 25, "type": "fact", "text": "They don't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 26, "type": "value", "text": "Enough is enough.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 27, "type": "policy", "text": "Take the burden of proof off the consumer and place it with the party that legally owns the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "756", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "By the time a file reaches litigation, the debtor has already received at least one prior opportunity to resolve the debt with the collector (the initial demand letter, which by law must inform the debtor of his/her right to challenge the veracity of the debt being pursued).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "By making default judgment more difficult, the CFPB would only be rewarding the debtors who choose to take no action to resolve their complaints.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Furthermore, the CFPB arguably has no authority to impose new, more burdensome requirements upon litigants in state court fora.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Doing so would constitute an admission that state court rules of civil procedure deny due process in other types of proceedings that are not granted the \"benefit\" of Federal oversight.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "808", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "The debt collector who harassed me did that number one on the \"three others\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I got calls saying \"hey we'll settle for\" such and such.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was a medical debt ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and I was tempted to say why? ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "There is only going to be more medical debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "When times are that difficult for people, making the mortgage and getting medicine takes precedence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "I don't think it should be legal for any of these things to happen,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "and certainly not robo-repeat calling", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "but yet as you read these comments they are going on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "I hope this has a good outcome and there will be laws and fines for those companies that do this,", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "because what is available now, suing the debt collector, has not put a dent in their egregious behavior.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1262", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There needs to be rules around how disputes are handled for people with the same or similar names.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "There needs to be a process for disputing incorrect information on a credit report as well as for handling mistaken identity with the courts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "739", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Please READ this article about global debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Enforcing the existing debt collection paradigm simply legitimizes and illegitimate system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["4"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "PLEASE DO MORE than that,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Please LEVEL THE DEBT PLAYING FIELD.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://seekingalpha.com/article/1832102-global-debt-elephant-in-the-room?source=google_news\"> GLOBAL DEBT ELEPHANT IN THE ROOM.</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1374", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a banker in a small bank, I have been on both sides of the collection business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Bankers have to prove a debt and give consumers a chance of object to the validity.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "When I have had collection agencys contact us for medical collections, I found these people to be scum.", "reasons": ["3", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They don't care if the debt is valid, correct, or anything else.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "They just know that they get 50% of everything they collect.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "You can request that they not contact you again, but they will.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "My suggestion is that collection agencies not be allowed to call at all and all correspondence be in writing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "If anyone can tell me what I owe and why I owe it, I will pay it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "They can't and they don't care.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1087", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Providing too much information in the first notice creates a risk of divulging sensitive personal information to the person who now lives where the actual debtor used to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "I do think that providing the chain of ownership information (especially original creditor) should be provided for sold debts.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "When it comes to medical debts, HIPPA becomes another concern.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Therefore, specific info on medical debts should only be provided AFTER the collector has verified that they are communicating with the proper party.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "540", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I can understand 1 call. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "But thats it!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "And they better not talk a out my debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But I can see them wanting to make sure they have the right number by verifying with a relative or neighbor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Especially with that ridiculous FOTI thing they say on my voicemail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "393", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "That's not true in my experience.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Unethical debt collectors just ignore requests now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Most consumers also don't know ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "that debt collectors can call you to collect a debt on any phone number you have used to contact the company or provided the company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "So calling your credit card company from your best friend's home phone, your neighbor's phone, or your relative's house puts their phone numbers on your contact list.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "This practice needs to be changed to protect the confidentiality of the debt collection process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "380", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "When mortgage holders transfer servicing of a mortgage loan to another creditor, they have rules in place as to informing the consumer that their loan has been sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Apply the same standards to any debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1220", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "From 1999 - 2004 I worked on a number of online identity authentication initiatives.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "At that time the only available solution was to ask \"out of wallet\" questions based on the consumer's credit file.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "For example, the credit report might show that the consumer lived on Elm Street 20 years ago.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Since an old address would not be easy to find (e.g. in a lost wallet) ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "the idea is that if the consumer knows that they lived on Elm Street 20 years ago, there is greater confidence that this is indeed the person that they claim to be.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The problem with this approach is that the information in credit reports has a reliability problem.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Reports indicating low error rates are misleading:", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "they only look to \"material errors\" ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "and they are often funded by credit industry groups.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "If it is commonly accepted that credit reports are filled with errors - then it is incumbent upon collectors to validate and verify the debt prior to pulling a credit report or contacting the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "694", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "You raise an issue that has two distinct definitions: \"sent\" and \"received\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think that any consumer wishes that they \"receive\" a notice that wasn't \"sent\" in the first place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "In addition, letters and parcels get lost in the mail all the time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "If there is a requirement for a credit/collector to \"send\" the notices you are referring to, the first place to send them are going to be an address that is on file.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If the letters then get returned, then you would know that they are not at the address that is on file.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "But the letters have to be \"sent\" in the first place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "815", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree that of course an ideal situation would be for consumers not to pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "But let's not let the perfect be the enemy of the good.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I was proposing some viable method that would result in an ability of a consumer to have a hearing.", "reasons": ["3_4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Hearings cost money", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and ultimately the collector would be assessed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1255", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Off the top, I believe NYC has similar laws where business are not allowed to charge extra for the use of credit cards", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "however it seems online payments to the city (taxes, water bill, traffic ticket, etc) using a credit card are still assessed a processing fee.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It seems NYC itself is confused about this.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "657", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "My experience is only with medical bills.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The debt collectors seem only to know (a) what hospital and (b) how much.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "When you've been doing the hokey-pokey from emergency room to nursing home and back again over a period of months, that information is not much help.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "What's really needed is an itemized bill that's a lot clearer than the \"statement of benefits\" we get now. Something as clear as: \"You were in X hospital on this date. You had this test and that test. They cost a gazillion dollars, but we bargained them down to $17.48. Please pay this amount.\"", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "656", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If a debt is to be turned over to a collection agency, the owner of the debt should be required to send a fully itemized statement to the debtor.", "reasons": ["2", "3", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The statement should have a large-type header, something like, \"[NAME OF CREDITOR] IS TURNING THIS DEBT OVER TO [NAME], A DEBT COLLECTION AGENCY.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This would give the debtor another chance to pay in the simplest way, before getting tangled up in idiot phone calls,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and it would help the debtor identify the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The debt owner already has the itemized bill;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "it would be just a matter of copying it again and sending it.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "there should be a requirement that the original creditor make a true, good-faith effort to contact the debtor.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've dealt with those who do this, and those who don't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Some will send you a bill, and then when they get no answer, call you and check the address, which is often wrong.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Some, it seems, hardly wait for the ink to dry on their first bill before they turn it over to collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "495", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The FTC got this one right.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Alternative one is easy to communicate and understand.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Terms like default and charge-off can be confusing and subject to interpretation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "397", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "As a creditor, I can agree with this notification on medical services", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "since most people receive bills from companies they never heard of.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "When it comes to auto loans, and other monthly installment loans, I am sure the consumers are aware of the debt and who it is payable to, unless sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This could be a huge regulatory burden on creditors that don't sell loans and follow current collection laws.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "After all, do very many people pay monthly payment to the same people for several months and them forget they owe the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "All laws should not apply to all creditors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "586", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I once had a debt collector send collection letters to my work address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They had my home address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I think this should also be prohibited.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Who gets personal mail sent to them at work?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "560", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There needs to be some federal protections for the consumer and a clear appeals process.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The state run by private company programs seem to see the alleged debtor as already guilty.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "For example, some consumer groups have suggested that entities may not be including a \"clear and conspicuous statement\" that the consumer may dispute the validity of the alleged bad check violation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "What kind of financial incentives are there for these companies to meet certain benchmarks that may not be in the consumer's best interest?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It kind of sounds like those arbitration programs for credit card debt where everything was stacked in the favor of the creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1075", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Someone keeps calling for a person named Sean, who does not live here and I don't know anyone by that name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I tell them they have the wrong number, but they continue to call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They sometimes leave canned messages on my answering machine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "I realize some debtors pretend not to be at the number being called, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "but these collectors need to verify the information ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "so they don't keep calling the wrong number.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I don't know if the debtor gave the wrong number intentionally, or this number was used by someone else before I got it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It is extremely irritating.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "And even though the callers do not say they are debt collectors, it is obvious.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1056", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "In order to get a default judgment through a State Court, a collector's pleadings have to spell out the theory of their case (usually contract) with sufficient specificity that a reasonable person can understand the basis for the claim.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Without some form of affidavit from the actual creditor, very few courts will award a default judgment.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Also, most state court approved forms are already written for the \"least sophisticated debtor.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I don't see any reason to impose a more stringent standard on collection lawsuits than are imposed on any other lawsuit.", "reasons": ["0", "1", "2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "419", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should not be allowed to dispute a debt using identity theft as a reason without proof as well.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise some consumers will \"game\" the system and make false disputes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "906", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers generally have no notice and do not know that a debt has been sold until checking their credit report or until a collection agency calls to collect a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Being notified of a debt being sold, would at least allow the consumer to verify who is actually the owner of a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I once paid a debt to a collection agency, only to find that I had paid one of 3 collection agencies who claimed to own the debt).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "With regards to costs, most consumers and most debt buyers are unable to detail how a 2200.00 debt becomes a 7000.00+ debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "And I found that very few even knew the original creditor's name, yet still attempted to collect this debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "The new rule should at minimum state the Original Creditor's name, and that Debt Buyer has purchased the right to collect the debt.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This would allow the consumer to verify that a debt buyer has the right to collect the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1342", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to see some strict regulation on the number of times a creditor can call in a given period of time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Capital One Bank's dialers will call every single hour if a payment is overdue...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "sometimes these things are simply overlooked.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "If I know I am paying bills on a given day, I just use my caller ID and ignore them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "I do think that these calls need to be at least limited.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It comes down to simple harrasment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "970", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Many disputes are difficult to investigate ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "because it is unclear what the consumer's dispute actually is.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If the consumer is specific enough so that there is a clear item to research, we will do so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "However, its a vague dispute such as \"I dispute this debt\" or \"I don't owe this debt\" (which is incredibly common), then we will provide statements or a contract to attempt to address it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The amount of the investigation is largely lead by the amount of detail the consumer relays,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and most of it results in us relying on the documentation the creditor provides to resolve the dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Sometimes we may need to ask the creditor to research their records for indication of X, Y, or Z,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "but most the time the dispute isn't that specific.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I find in my practice that we will often ask a consumer to provide information to support their dispute (such as proof of payment), but then the consumer does not provide it, and we are stuck in our efforts to investigate further.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Requiring only a \"reasonable\" investigation without further definition sounds like a punt to the courts to decide the defintion after a lot of litigation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I think at least a broad definition of obtaining documentation to support the position that consumer owes the debt/amount/and creditor is a good place to start.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "I would love to see consumers use a form letter prepared by the CFPB which spells out a variety of disputes and helps them articulate the dispute better.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "I do think one of the toughest hurdles for a collector (and one of the biggest complaints from persons against whom collection efforts are made) is when they get a person that states the debt is not theirs (but someone else's ) with the same name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "We do our homework on our end to investigate ", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["14", "15"]}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "(we'll attempt to compare the last 4 digits of the social, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "we may run a skip trace to see if party we contacted lived at the address on the statements, etc", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "and we will provide verification,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "but in a mobile world investigating that the John Smith you contacted is the same John Smith you are attempting to resolve a debt with can prove tricky.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "This is especially tricky if there is NEVER indication that we have reached the wrong person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "value", "text": "We never wish to contact the wrong party regarding a debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "fact", "text": "but it unfortunately happens ", "reasons": ["21"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "fact", "text": "because consumers don't always relay updated contacted information to creditors and a collector then has to rely upon the best information available to them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "value", "text": "Unfortunately, I don't know what the fix is here.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "value", "text": "Despite the stories to the contrary, it simply is not the intent of any professional and responsible collection agency or firm to attempt collections from a party that does not owe the debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "value", "text": "but this is a hard one to address without good communication from the wrongly contacted party and the collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "851", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "With increased and onerous liability for making calls and sending letters to debtors, creditors and debt buyers have had little option but to file suit rather than repeatedly attempt to contact an uncooperative or uncommunicative debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Most complaints provide adequate and identifying information about the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "In my experience, most debtors don't feel taken advantage of by lawsuits,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "they simply understand they owe the debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "so there is little point in filing an answer or taking time to appear in court.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "In fact, the vast majority never respond to a Federal Law letter inviting them to dispute the debt.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Filing suits and appearing in court is expensive and time consuming for creditors and debt buyer,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "but there is little alternative,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "nor should there be", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "as these matters have always been governed appropriately by State law and State judges.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "and the US is a credit ecomony", "reasons": ["11_12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "over 70% of our economy is based on consumer spending ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "fact", "text": "which comes mainly from credit extensions and not consumers pay increases),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "there are simply more defaults,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "particularly in a Great Recession.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "Any heavy handed Federal regulation will hamper and restrict credit granting and debt buying,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "both of which are needed by the economy and the credit industry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "policy", "text": "While credit grantors should should make their documentation retention systems more accessible and share more documents upon a sale of accounts,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "policy", "text": "a lack of documentation should not hamper State court lawsuits when a debtor offers no dispute so long as the account is adequately identified in a complaint.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "value", "text": "In Michigan, efforts to \"make it more likely that consumers would defend themselves\" have fell very flat for the reasons mentioned above.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "As it has always been, the protections are in place and are used by those debtors that wish to avail themselves of them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "value", "text": "Judges are there to listen.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "value", "text": "However, most debtors (bless them) understand they simply owe the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1318", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I received several Robo calls leaving messages to have me served at my job on a debt I do not owe.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They have Threatened me via voice mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They also use Voip numbers we have reversed them different each time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have reported them several times ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "but they continue to call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "492", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was following the advice of our bankruptcy attorney.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was allowed to tell creditors only a limited amount of information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I could confirm- my identify, that yes I owed the debt, and third that I was not able to start repaying my debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "No I was not allowed to tell the debt collectors that we would be filing bankruptcy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "It took almost six months to complete tasks prior to notifying creditors about the bankruptcy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "During that time I was subjected to verbal abuse, threats, illegal intimidation tactics, and outright lies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "The tape recorder completely stopped the bad behavior.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It's amazing what debt collectors will say and do when they call debtors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "It's a totally different story what they want recorded.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "The best money you will ever spend is a cheap $20-25 telephone tape recorder.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "929", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The current penalty for violating the FDCPA is \"not less than $100 and up to $1000.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Further, the violations cannot be \"stacked\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "so those violating the law 10 times on one debt, will generally only face the maximum of a $1000 penalty.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Punitive damages are hard to prove.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "A $1000 penalty is not a deterrent to the debt collection industry,and too low to get most attorney's interest is taking these cases.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "If we want to see the law upheld, raise the penalty to $10,000 per violation", "reasons": ["4", "6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "and you'll see most of these characters clean up their act and stop using abusive collection tactics.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "766", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "After offering documentation that I didn't owe a debt, the collection company ignored what I offered as proof and continued to try to collect the debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "even stated they didn't care that I didn't owe it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "They should be required to investigate and respond in writing to a consumer's defense,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so a follow up can be made, or complaint filed with a governmental agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Documentation should also follow the claim ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "as collection companies sell their lists to new companies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Better, no documented defense of a claim should be eligible for sale until resolved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "930", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Give Consumers Fair Notice and A Chance to Bid on Their Own Debts When Banks Sell Defaulted Obligations to Debt Buyers", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "When a consumer falls behind on loan or credit card payments, the bank often \"sells\" the account to a debt buying company for a few pennies on the dollar.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Debt buyers contribute nothing to society.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Yet, they are allowed to obtain windfall profits by pursuing impoverished consumers for the full face value of such debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This is unfair.", "reasons": ["2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "If a bank is going to sell a consumer\"s debt for pennies on the dollar, the bank should be required to notify that consumer, and allow that consumer a fair chance to bid on and purchase his/her own debt, on terms just as favorable as the terms offered to any other debt buyer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I hope the CFPB will consider new rules in this regard.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Please note there is currently a petition on the White House website for this issue at:", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "reference", "text": "https://petitions.whitehouse.gov/petition/give-consumers-fair-notice-and-chance-bid-their-own-debts-when-banks-sell-defaulted-obligations-debt/FRMdMMxb", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "It was initiated here:", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.californiacollectiondefense.com/please-sign-petition-allow-consumers-buy-debts/", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1061", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I think the 9-8 is a typo.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have seen other typos on this site too, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and they provide to FDCPA link that shows it is 8-9, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so no big deal.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "On this topic though, I would like to see the 8-9 changed to 9-8.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "8 is too early and 9 is too late at night to get phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "958", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The burden of proof should be on the creditor.", "reasons": ["1", "1_2", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If you make the debtor responsible for following up with a request, it gives the creditor an opportunity to say they never received anything from the debtor...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If they had to send the documents to start with, there would not be any question.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "938", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree with josephusmyer.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Our son ran up small debts at several stores and banks around eight years ago.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Debt-collectors (debt-buyers) have contacted him and threatened him with legal action on time-barred debts (without notifying him of the status).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "998", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The collection agency is not required to actually validate the debt and provide information to the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Example, I disputed a debt as valid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "The return validation consisted of a one line sentence: \"The consumer owes the debt.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This is not to me or to any reasonable person validation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "The collection agency should be required to at least furnish enough information to allow the consumer to recognize or dispute the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "That information ideally would be a copy of the original application and a copy of the final billing statement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "231", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Collectors are responsible for re-establishing contact with delinquent customers and providing services that facilitate repayment of the loans, regardless of the technology utilized.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "In Collections, automated dialing systems effectively increase the ability for the collector to reach delinquent customers unwilling to proactively reach out to the creditors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Automated dialing systems are used in many other ways not related to debt collection: telemarketers use them to reach potential customers, schools use them to notify parents of closings due to inclement weather.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The technology is the same", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but the intent is different based on the user.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The Telephone Consumer Protection Act (TCPA) prohibits creditors from using automated dialing systems to call cell phone numbers without consent from the customer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The TCPA\"s original purpose, protecting consumers from costly charges as a result of automated calls, has been subsumed by the new goal of preventing overly numerous call attempts to a number that (generally) is directly connected to the customer.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It does not change the purpose of collection calls, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "it merely makes the process less efficient.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Regulating which numbers can be called using an automated dialing system is also counter to the growing reality of wireless-only households.", "reasons": ["10_11", "12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "According to the Center for Disease Control's 'Wireless Substitution' latest report (Early release data, July-December 2012), over one third (36%) of adults in the United States live in a household with only wireless telephone service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "That figure is even higher (45%) when you look at children living in the US.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "With an average annualized growth rate of 34%, it is conceivable that sometime before 2020 only a minority of the country's adults will be living in households with a landline telephone that can be autodialed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should allow for the autodialing of all telephone numbers provided by the customer without byzantine consent requirements.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "Regardless of whether it is at application or during the course of normal business, once the number is provided by the customer to the creditor, that number should be considered another viable option for collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1070", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Let's remember that most debtors have had the original creditor from 2 to 4 collection agencies and the creditors attorneys office before a suit is ever filed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "That process usually takes as much a 2 years or more.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "So it is difficult to think that the courts should make special accommodations for these individuals.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Every person called into court has had many opportunities to have the debt validated or payment arrangements made prior to a default judgment.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "I do believe basic evidence should be supplied.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "This would be a statement or bill copy with a matching name of the consumer and proof of address at the time the debt was incurred.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This proof of address could be provided by other confirming data available through skip tracing companies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "There were significant problems with how debt buyers were allowed to file suit and receive default judgments with virtually no evidence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "So improvements and consistency is needed in evidence but it should also not be expected to show every single bill copy.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "357", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Some people are concerned that collectors don't do much more than doublecheck that the amount in the validation notice is what the creditor says the consumer owes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "THAT'S ALL THEY DO.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "They never do anything of substance to actually push back on the creditor's claims.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've had actual documentation that disputes creditor's claims, and all collectors do is rely on the information given them to by creditors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The CFPB is no better.", "reasons": ["5", "6_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "My experience with them was much the same as dealing with a collector.", "reasons": ["6_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "The CFPB did nothing to verify or investigate the creditor's claims;", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "they simply took the creditor's claims as outright facts despite conflicting documentation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1244", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Partial payments should NOT revive the debt.", "reasons": ["1", "2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The original lender or the agencies working on their behalf have more than reasonable time to collect on an outstanding amount owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "We have rules in place on both collecting debts and on reporting them", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "and partial payment on a debt should not circumvent those rules.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1144", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is a fantastic idea.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Right now, debt buyers buy debt for an average price of 4 cents on the dollar.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Many debts are bought for 2-4 cents on the dollar", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and many other debts are given away for free.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If I were an original creditor, would like to get the most money I could for a debt owed to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "And so if I could get 10 cents on the dollar directly from the debtor, rather than 4 cents on the dollar from a debt buyer, then I would see no reason not to offer a significantly reduced debt settlement rate to the debtor (or as you call it, letting consumers bid on their own debt).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Right now, original creditors offer no significant reduced rate to debtor before selling for 4 cents on the dollar.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Most creditors barely even offer debtors 10% off the debt as a settlement offer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Sure, a creditor could more quickly offload portfolios to debt buyers by selling them at 4 cents on the dollar.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "But creditors could also make way more money offering a onetime chance at 10 cents on the dollar (or something really attractive but still more than 4 cents on the dollar).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "Perhaps the CFPB should make a rule that allows consumers/debtors the chance to receive a onetime offer that is valid for only X amount of days (maybe 45 days) from the date of the letter sent from their creditors of a significantly reduced rate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "The offer would only be valid for a short amount of time and would also inform the consumer that, should the consumer not accept the offer, the creditor would then turn it over to a debt buyer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "This letter would only be sent if the creditor\"s intentions are to sell the debt and not just another attempt to collect.", "reasons": ["13", "14"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "So that this way it gives the consumer one final chance to clear the debt owed", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "and the creditors also have less loss and more profits and would be able to lend to more consumers, give better rates to consumers, and stimulate the economy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "Because more money that is changing hands at higher values (10 cents on the dollar vs. 4 cents on the dollar) instead of sitting in the accounts receivable section waiting to be collected (one day, if ever) stimulates the economy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "This rule would not negatively impact anything (or anyone) and only positively impacts everyone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "One minor impact might be on the debt collection industry possibly receiving less debt in their portfolios that they buy,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "but this minor impact is offset by the large positive impacts on the economy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1189", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "There is no need for these so-called examiners", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but there is definitely a need for courageous and dedicated attorneys determined to enforce the laws that the CFPB should pass, laws that protect the ordinary folk, the innocent, those who're unable to protect themselves, even those who may have actually failed to pay their bills", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "because our constitution guarantees the right to our innocence unless proven guilty.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "We cannot allow expediency to deny us such fundamental rights.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "I believe there is such a thing as the Gideon Decision by the Supreme Court that provides for any accused to an adequate defence,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "so if any debt-collector or creditor for that matter denies the alleged debtor the right to have his day in court or to a proper defence, then the CFPB attorneys should come down hard on such violators.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "The principle behind any rules promulgated by the CFPB must ensure that no alleged debtor get bullied into paying up or blind-sided by the court into doing so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Sometimes, there are reasons why the outstanding bills are not paid ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "and the consumer should be allowed to confront the creditor to resolve any complaints by the consumer before the bills are paid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It's a very straight-forward and simple situation actually.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "All the CFB needs to do is to enact basic regulations that protects the consumer and stipulates very clearly that the burden of proof must be borne by the creditor before any debt-collector can be engaged to pursue such debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "The debt-collector must only be allowed to follow specific guidelines when doing so", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "and the matter should be referred to a small claims court to have both sides plead their case before the court issues a ruling, rather than to allow the claim to be reported to a credit reporting agency ", "reasons": ["13"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "that will destroy the credit score or rating of the consumer without his knowledge, which is absolutely wrong.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "Only lawful and valid debts, i.e. when a judgment order has been made, should be allowed to be reported to any credit reporting agency, to avoid creditors and debt-collectors from using such agencies to damage the interests of alleged debtors with unfounded or unproven debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "568", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have already spoken with an attorney.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "This is how I found out about the separation of state and federal law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Because I was sued in state civil court is why my validation requests were ignored by the plaintiffs as well as the seating judge.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "What I should have done (in state court) was sent a 'discovery' request AFTER the case had been filed rather then a validation request.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Please note - the 'collection agency' was a large legal firm.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "They knew the laws well and whereas I was a lay person and not versed in law , I was like a sitting duck just waiting for the slaughter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "If I did take them to court I would receive hundreds but it would cost me thousands....", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I just do not have that type of money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "What really touched my heart was sitting in that court room and seeing others that also thought that the law would be fair if they represented themselves.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "Needless to say, we all lost and lost big time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I asked the judge why would he allow this when the plaintiff was a unlicensed collection agency and he stated ' they look like attorneys to me'.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "I knew that at that point I had lost my case.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "394", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "The majority of the clients I work with try to settle their accounts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The main issue is that most of the collection companies will not provide the client with a letter of agreement until after the payment is made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "They also will often wait weeks for a receipt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have even had clients tell me that the company required a $10.00 payment for the receipt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1037", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I just want to add that I am not advocating getting out of the debt because of a life changing event.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I am advocating that the debt be frozen at the amount it was at the time of the involuntary default and then paid back even if it takes ten years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1316", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have had debt collectors call and tell me that I am not cooperating to get the debt resolved, yell at me, tell me I must be lazy or not understand I owe the money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They have called me from 7:00 am to 9:00pm at least 10 times during the day using a different company name, different phone number and location including my city and other cities and states all in the same day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I tell them I am a senior they tell me to borrow the money from a family member or friend.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I tell them I am not going to do that the harrassment starts all over.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Many of them call and act like I am an old friend before they tell me who they are.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "They threaten to ruin my credit raiting, confiscate my home and belonging and car,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The most annoying is when they call and I answer they hang up and call again an hr later and hang up again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I know it is them ", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I have caller id.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "722", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers who ask for validation should receive just that: a validation that the agency has verified the balance due has some basis as alleged.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Too often consumers categorize this process as requiring \"proof\" as taxguy does.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This is not the function of the validation process.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "\"Proof\" is something that will occur in court (or not).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "No document will be enough \"proof\" for many consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "That is why the court system exists.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "584", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was sent to collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Collector informed me that it was for and overdue insurance payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Having everything on Auto-Pay, I overlooked the notice they mailed to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "One call to my agent and the problem was resolved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I'm glad they called and gave me the opportunity to get to root of problem before it jeopardized my good credit rating!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "I \"know\" the majority of CFPB complaints come from people who simply don't want to pay their bill.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I know this ", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I have worked for a collection agency for the last twenty years, privy to all complaints we receive and very, very few have any merit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "I'm by no means stating that some people don't have legitimate complaints.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "What I am saying is if we compare the number of complaints to the number of accounts being pursued by all collection agencies the percentage of complaints would be a mere fraction of one percent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "So, how much more regulation is necessary to address such a tiny percentage?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "461", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The consumer should be allowed to record all calls for proof of conversation with collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "And once a collector received a notice to not contact a debtor at their workplace it should be required that they do not even for \"location\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "822", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was sued for an alleged debt from 1993 by NYC landlord.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Judge denied him the 1600.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and then his real estate/collections attorney put me into collections ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and the landlord got to write off a debt that was not a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Great for these big landlords in NYC ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "as they play the corporate game and sue a tenant 10 times and write it off each and every time even though its not a valid debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Its a big deal in Manhattan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "414", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "security would be paramound.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Since the weaknesses in current authentication practices financial institutions/others covered by FACTA and the FCRA are not within the scope of this legislation,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "it shouldn't be difficult to impose those same security standards on any centralized debt collection database.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "517", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Innocent until proven guilty is the American Justice System.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "And the burden of the proof is on the one bringing the suit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt collectors need to get their act together before trying to file frivolous lawsuits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "201", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "When an attorney is a 'Debt Collector' (as per their own documents) and not legally considered a 'Collection Agency' the attorney is not held accountable for consumer protection law violations (both local and federal) within civil court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "This loop hole needs to be addressed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The attorneys/debt collectors are not monitored by the state bar", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "because it is a collection practice ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "(the attorneys buy old debt and then collect upon that debt in civil court", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "and the state and federal civil courts are not monitoring the attorneys", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "because it is an attorneys office and not considered a collection agency ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "- even though the attorneys buy old debt then take alleged debtors to civil court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I personally know of a very large attorney agency in Washington State that even gives classes thru the Washington state bar to other attorneys", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "because it is a easy caseload to win.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1281", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I left a long comment about one particular collector, but recently was harassed by yet another one who was trying to collect from someone else who was not me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Their caller ID was not a phone number;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "it was just the names of different states, but turned out to be the same company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "These people are bottom-feeders with no scruples.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Accurate caller ID should be required ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "so the victim can at least identify the collector and have a call-back number for them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "And monetary penalties should be much, much stiffer to discourage their outrageous, predatory and harassing practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Harrassment is part of their business models.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "These people are scum and should be required at the very least to identify themselves accurately.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "Robo-calls and ID spoofing should be illegal with stiff fines.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "989", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Because it it the consumer's phone ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "and that is their right!", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Why should the consumer pay to be harassed?!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Put the cost of doing this business where it belongs, which is on the companies not the consumers!", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I pay for my cell phone,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I pay for the minutes,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I am the person that will decide how they are used and who will call me, not these shady, nasty companies!", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1089", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As for medical collections, I very, very rarely see a legitimate dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["1", "2"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Most often people are just trying to get the item removed from their credit or scare the collector with threats of FDCPA action.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Many of the disputes we receive are copied directly from the internet and contain all kinds of demands for proof that are not required by any state or federal law OR even the rules of evidence during trial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "CFPB really needs to address this issue and set a clear standard for what is (or is not) a legitimate dispute and how the collector should respond.", "reasons": ["0", "1", "2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1018", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Unfortunately, a few of the suggestions you made would actually violate the FDCPA.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt collectors are not permitted to \"overshadow\" the validation notice by giving consumers deadlines, making demands for payments, or giving settlement offers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Further, I don't believe consumers need a \"sample\" dispute notice.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "If the consumer truly has a disagreement or dispute with the debt being collected, he or she should be able to articulate that dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "993", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Most companies have a strict \"NO PERSONAL CALLS\" policy;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "hence the act should include a clause that \"...unless specifically allowed, in writing, by the debtor, a collector is barred from attempting to contact a debtor at his/her place of employment.\"", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "842", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Only one out of my numerous collectors for my kids took me off their lists after I told them my son hasn't lived with me for over 20 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I also stated he owes me money also.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "My other 10 collectors keep calling ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "but I quit answering ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I recognize their phone numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "212", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do NOT owe any debt but have a COMMON FIRST and LAST NAME.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "My Constitutional rights are violated every time a lawyer fails to perform due diligence, per rule 137, BEFORE SIGNING and FILING COURT PAPER against me.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The clerks are helpless, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "the judges & attorney disciplinary do nothing favoring \"lawyer zealousness.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I then have to spend time & money, going to court to prove I am NOT the person who owes the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "I urge the CFPB to create mechanisms for clerks & citizens that make it 1) easier to fix these messes &, 2) to bring sanctions against lawyers & judges for MISUSE OF LEGAL PROCEDURE, ABUSE OF PROCESS, WRONGFUL CIVIL PROCEEDINGS, & MALICIOUS PROSECUTION.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1077", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I live in Georgia which seems to have laws that are very biased toward the debt owner.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "An example is the statutes of limitations for Mortgage debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "For instance, if the 1st lienholder forecloses, and you have a 2nd mortgage also, the 2nd remains in effect", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The OCGA states that the statute of limitations for any \" debt instrument under seal\", is 20 years from the date of foreclosure.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The 2nd lien can be sold over and over ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "and the last one holding it can come after you for up to 20 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "In these times when houses are lost due to catastrophic illness, job loss and other situations that not due to the irresponsibility of the homeowner, legislation should be drafted to protect the consumer from financial ruin.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "518", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "That's the price of being in the business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "If debt collectors can't hack it in the real world, then they need to find another business industry to be for their \"careers.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "576", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "When two parties engage in a lawsuit, each side presents the evidence they have supporting their assertions.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a collector, I provide proof of the debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The debtor is also expected to present some proof that the debt is not theirs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Yes, the assumption is innocent until proven guilty but you have to provide evidence to support your claim of innocence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "If I offer a signed document that says you agreed to the purchase and documentation that supports that you did not pay, I have fulfilled my side of the burden of proof.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The debtor also bears a burden of proof in our system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "That's what the judge is for - to hear both sides, weigh the evidence, and make a fair decision based on the evidence and arguments presented.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "194", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Recently, courts have held that debt collectors can escape 1692i's venue provisions entirely by pursuing debt collection through arbitration instead.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "As the NAF studies reflect, arbitration has not proven a satisfactory alternative.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I urge the CFPB to include in a rule language interpreting 1692i as requiring debt collectors to proceed in court, not through largely-unregulated arbitral forums.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "659", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think probably the benefits of giving debt collectors and buyers access to these documents would NOT worth the costs unless the documents have to be included with the validation notice.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If the debt collectors were anxious to be sure they had the right debtor, sure, great.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "But I don't think they are.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The actual guy on the phone is only anxious to get the money;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "he doesn't really care where it comes from or whether the debt is legal.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Giving him the information, without giving it to the debtor, probably wouldn't be much good.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "And maybe I'm being unfair.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Maybe these companies are strict about making sure the debt is collected from the right person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Naaah....", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "529", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Text me please...", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "it is annoying to have to ignore your call every other day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "For goodness sake it is 2013!!!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Send me a text and wait for my reply.", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I cant take calls at work and ignore calls from numbers I dont know.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Which makes it easy for me to be in collections and not know.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "If you have my cell number because the bank had it please use it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Send me a text and tell me who you are why youre calling.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "If not I wont answer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1252", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Email correspondences from a company or collection agency should list the state they are registered in and the registration number for consumer validation purposes.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There is way to many scam emails to possibly think an email from a collector would be valid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "901", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "For over 3 years I have been contacted by debt collectors for an alleged debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I diligently send proof of payment and am ignored, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and several months later a new firm sends the same letter re the same debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "The collector never responds, investigates or verifies the dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "They should be forced to do so.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1332", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have dealt with the issue of disputes ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "and when you file a dispute and it as been closed it is placed in the comment section that you have filed a dispute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "By doing this, this has kept me from refinancing my home ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "just because the word dispute was there.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "The mortgage company said I had to have this removed,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "so I filed another form to ask for this to be removed it never was.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "I believe that once the dispute has been closed there should be no indication that there was a dispute filed.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "You again get penalized for trying to correct mistakes on your report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "Another issue that has come up regarding when an account has been charged off or in my case a repossession of a vehicle I had turn over due to not being released by my doctor to go back to work and my disability ran out , I had no other choice but to hand the vehicle over.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "then 6 years later I received a 1099 for over $6000.00.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "Plus the 16% interest they charged me for 4 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "We keep paying these high interest rates ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "but yet we still have to pay for our credit scores and only receive one free report a year,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "policy", "text": "If we are trying to stay on top of credit fraud and inaccurate information that is not of our doing but from reporting agencies , these agencies should be putting more funds in for these things.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "910", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I understand your concern and desire to stop the calls that are not for you.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "No one should be spoken to with disrespect.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I dislike the fact that there isn't a clearinghouse of sorts for phone numbers that would help eliminate the needless calls.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Of course how would you stop a responsible party from adding their number to the NOT responsible list?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It is also unproductive for collection calls to be made to wrong party consumers.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "There isn't a benefit to anyone to spend time making these calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "There are many rules and regulations to keep collection agencies honest and legal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "And there are consequences if they don't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Do you know of any consequences to someone who gives out a bad phone number, address or even a name?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "I think we should all ban together to restore integrity in the world of credit and stop making excuses for people who want to get out of paying.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "489", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Creditors generally do not send accounts to collection until after they have sent multiple notices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Requiring a specific notice will expose small creditors to liability beyond any benefit to consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "462", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am concerned that there is some type of rewards system in place that somehow monetizes those who report when a consumer has a potential bad credit scenario.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "As a conspiracy theory it makes sense since it drives up the cost of a loan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "594", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am a clerk at a local city court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am the civil clerk ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and I feel that debtors are treated extremely unfairly by debt collection laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The Court cannot give legal advice", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "so it is saddening to have to try and explain and console upset litigants who have no idea what they are in for.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "I think there should be more avenues for pro se litigants who cannot afford to retain a private attorney ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "(which is 95 % of the litigants in my city).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "I can say that most people do not answer summonses because they either were not properly served or they just straight up do not care, or most often, do not understand the legalese.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "BUT, I do have to say that I get many litigants who call and ask what they do now that they are served.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "On the occasions that people do file answers, most of them are in letter form, not a \"legal\" verified answer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "Most debt collection attorneys jump right on that and request a summary judgment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "Our Court does not turn away letters, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "and we send a copy to the attorney and set the matter up for a pre trial conference with a judge or court attorney to help try to get both parties together to come to some sort of resolution.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "fact", "text": "The Court does have to adhere to a scheduling policy for these conferences, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "but we are very flexible ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "if a defendant has a scheduling conflict we try to accommodate them as best we can.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "fact", "text": "When summonses are filed with the court, half of them have tons of information about the debt, others only have the amount due!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "I find that sometimes it's hard for litigants to obtain further proving documents from attorneys, even with the court telling them they have to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "When entering default judgments, I take my time and examine the whole file, like comparing the contents of the summons/complaint and the default judgment submitted, re-checking the affidavit of service of the summons (to make sure the defendant had the legal time to answer the summons), and ensuring that attached to the default judgment is the proper documentation as to purchasing the debt, a non-military affidavit, etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "I also make sure that they are being charged the proper interest rate and court costs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "The bottom line is that the debtors still do not have enough and/or sufficient laws to protect them, and the Court's hands are tied based on these laws,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "value", "text": "even if they wanted to help, they couldn't.", "reasons": ["20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "value", "text": "I know the Court is to remain impartial, but in a small city, everybody knows everybody and sometimes it's hard to see these practices occurring.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "353", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "A separate \"summary of rights\" should be sent to, and made available, to consumers.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "We are woefully uninformed and misinformed about our rights as consumers; what avenues of negotiation we can pursue; or even who can assist us.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Furthermore, there should be some laws on the books on when collectors cannot collect", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "if the original creditor has not made an attempt to collect the debt for an extended period of time, I should not get a collection notice 20 years after the fact.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1307", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "My problem with those debt collection companies employees I have had to deal with is this...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "they either call themselves agent,investigators,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "or they are members of a special department investigating a debt alluding to Law Enforcement or DA's office.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Most recently, as last week, they have indicated, they are going to contact me at my place of employment and are going to initiate civil action if I don't contact them before the close of business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "This is out of order and should be stop", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "999", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Failure to properly validate the debt as described by furnishing final billing statement and original application would invoke the consumer's rights to have all further collection activity immediately barred and the ability of the consumer to have the debt IMMEDIATELY removed from their credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "All too often it takes years to have false or misleading information removed from a consumer's credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "335", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "As a consumer I should receive a notice or some type of warning that the debt will be turned over to a collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "And when there are a change in debt collectors, the consumer should be notified.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "762", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Several courts have held\"and the [FTC] and the [CFPB] agree'that a collector who sues or threatens suit on a time-barred debt violates the FDCPA.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The FDCPA prohibits, among other things, the use of \"any false, deceptive, or misleading representation or means in connection with the collection of any debt.\" ", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "These include making a false representation of 'the character, amount, or legal status of any debt,\" threatening 'to take any action that cannot legally be taken or that is not intended to be taken,\" and \"using any false or deceptive means to collect or attempt to collect any debt.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"id": 3, "type": "reference", "text": "http://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/201309_cfpb_agency-brief_12-cv-04057.pdf", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It is in fact your gross distortion of the law and misunderstanding to claim that SOL are a defensive mechanism to allow a plaintiff \"to avoid being disadvantaged\" for not filing a lawful suit within a lawful time frame.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "598", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do NOT answer any calls that have \"unknown caller\" or \"unknown\" in the ID.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If you can't show your name in the ID line, then something is not right with your company, or you have something to hide.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Remember, YOU are calling ME, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so in that sense, phone calls are an invasion of my privacy.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I don't have any obligation to answer any calls that I don't want to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a regulation that requires debt collection agencies to identify themselves when making phone calls.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "197", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "There is currently a split between the Ninth and First Circuits as to whether 1692i and other FDCPA provisions apply in garnishment proceedings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "In many states, the nominal defendant is the judgment debtor's employer,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "but the judgment debtor is the real party in interest.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "To allow consumers to better assert the defenses to and exemptions from garnishment available under state law, the CFPB should issue a rule applying 1692i to garnishment proceedings.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "217", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Allow the States and/or local courts administer lawsuits.", "reasons": ["1", "2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Regardless of any added rules, documents, etc. none will help increase debtors attending hearings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Since 1964 I have seen no significant increase of consumers attending hearings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have, however, seen the major reason being attributed to not understanding due process by consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1283", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "There are currently no \"teeth\" in the enforcement mechanism as well.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Right now filing complaints with the regulators does absolutely nothing except get you into some database ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "but nothing is every done about violations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Requiring accurate identification of the collector with a working call-back number should be the bare minimum.", "reasons": ["1_2", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "At least that way the consumer has a fighting chance of at least talking to them and trying to get erroneous calls stopped.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Right now government enforcement is non-existent and completely worthless.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "562", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Every debt I've ever had go in to collections has supposedly been given notice in advance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In the case of 2 hospital bills many years ago they claimed to have notified me by mail several times but I had never even received the initial bill let alone the follow ups.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Since I was insured at the time ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I only had to pay a reasonable co-pay and would have readily done so had I gotten the bills ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "(as additional information, in both cases I offered to pay at the time of visit and was told they only bill).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "This particular hospital has an \"in house\" collections department ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "so I get the impression that they often neglect to actually send info to patients so that they can then collect the additional fees and interest as profit.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "When a debt is turned to collections I feel it might be best if a mandatory 30 day notice outlining what the debt is for, previous contact attempts, amount due, available options such as payment plans and the exact effect of the collections process on the debt is sent to the person in a manner that is trackable and shows the intended recipient had the notice in their possession-perhaps a registered receipt type of delivery.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "424", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "my in-laws had the same issue with BoA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They paid their mortgate EARLY every month and still were reported as late every month.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This is tragic", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and ruined their credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "When these things happen it takes years for the credit to br repaired even though a collector reported the information falsely, incurracately, and repeatedly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "BoA should be penalized HEAVILY for these infractions", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "otherwise they just ignore consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "977", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If a bank or loan company makes the installment loan and does collections itself, and the debt is not sold or turned over to a collection agency, then there is no reason for a notice to the consumers to recognize the debt.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "They have been making payments to the debt collector for months and already know about the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Besides, the lender has already sent several past due statements and a certified letter about the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1303", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt collectors call and cannot verify that the creditor has merged with another company.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The debt may have written off the books of the acquired company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I propose that the CFPB implement a rule pertaining to debts written off by an acquired company and any additional stipulations on a timeframe to which an old debt can be collected only if the consumer has been validly notified that the debt has been sold to a debt collection agency; excluding the initial call from the DCA", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "564", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I'm in agreement with that statement.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Having worked for a Sheriff's Office where we served many debt collection processes, I found that not much effort is made to locate the proper address for the defendant.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "When we would find the defendant had moved, we would return it not found.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "However, the same cannot be said about private process servers who go out and post processes on the door without confirming they live there.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "883", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "My student loan company is giving me a ton of grief about allowing my husband to contact them regarding my student loan debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've filled out the same form about four times that is supposed to allow him to talk to them on my behalf ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "but any time they decide that they don't like dealing with him, they pull his authorization (sometimes mid-call) and refuse to talk to him about it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "He is never rude with them,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "he just doesn't put up with the run around my loan company gives me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "We never hear the same thing twice from them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Issues that are supposed to be taken care of rarely are and we are constantly told one thing by one rep and something completely different by the next.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1149", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Yes. I fell onto hard times during a divorce and found out a few years ago that my dad (whom I haven't lived with for 20+ years) receives so many debt collection calls for me every day he quit answering his home phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This is unacceptable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "We cannot even figure out how they got his phone number", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I never lived at that address at any point while I had those credit cards and he never co-signed any loans or credit cards with me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "The only connection we can come up with is that my stepmom co-signed a short term furniture loan for me 20 years ago when I was just out of college and that maybe somehow her name is tied to my credit report in some way", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "although I've never seen it on my credit reports.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "This is now 6 years after I went through my divorce ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "and he told me a few months ago he still gets several calls per week for me from debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Personally, I don't think they should be allowed to call ANY number for more than 3 months without successful contact with the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "Clearly, they don't have proof they've got the right number ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "and all they're doing by calling the same unverified number for 6 years is harrassing an innocent party.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "821", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a creditor who begins calling withing a few days of becoming past due.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They are relentless calling up to 10+ times a day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I don't call them back ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "because once on the phone with them, they hound you until you agree to make a payment or post-date a payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "If I don't call them within about 15 days of becoming past due, they start calling my relatives and neighbors and say \"we're trying to locate xxx - do you know them?\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "When they answer yes, they ask them to deliver a message to me (phone number and name).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've been told this is not illegal since they are using public information and not revealing who they are or what the call is in relation to, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "but this tactic is shameful.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "We are making an honest effort to get current and stay current, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "but when my neighbor hands me a piece of paper with a note on it, I feel pretty powerless.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "This is both harassment and abuse in my opinion", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "and it should be addressed.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "420", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I currently have an alias on my Credit report that I have NEVER gone by.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've disputed this serveral times ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I can't get this alias and the related debt off my report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "As such I want federal laws that REQUIRE an agency to produce some paperwork ,legal document that proves a consumer used that alias on a credit application/paperwork.", "reasons": ["0_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "When disputed with a CRA they should be requesting this information from the agencies as well.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "CRA's should be the neutral parties and be the enforcing agencies on both sides.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "CRA's should be mandated to report accurate information and be responsible to gather the accurate information.", "reasons": ["5", "7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "currently they are warehouses of bad information that err on the side of collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers do not have a reliable agency fighting for their rights.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "without enforcement Federal laws equate to a bunch of useless words on a paper.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "522", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I don't think that the partial SSN should be included.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "That raises too many privacy concerns.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "And I'm sure that one day a debt collection company will have a \"system malfunction\" and will \"accidentally\" send the full SSN.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Too many consumers have similar names in the same city.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Lastly, many different companies classify a partial SSN as the first 5 digits whereas other stick to the traditional last 4 digits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "If a mail thief is lurking, then he might have access to a consumers full SSN.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "359", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Some useful documents would be the last three collection notices ACTUALLY sent to the consumer.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Too many collection agencies have claimed they sent me regular notices regarding the debt when I have not have any contact with them for 2 - 3 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "But they claim they have \"records\" that claim otherwise.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Yet, there is no supporting documentation of such efforts. like say, copies of the notices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "305", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I would suggest a visit to the Federal Bankruptcy Rule 3001(effective 12/1/2012) and comments made during the proposed period, plus the hearing presentation statements published and are available.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The Rule already addresses documentation issues.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I again see that attaching all of the proposed documentation to the validation notice is not productive for the consumer or the sender.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I do believe additional documentation as to chain of title be available if a consumer is being sued in Court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1295", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "After a court verdict in favor of a debt collector, Banks assess a significant fee against a customer when a customer's account is levied by the debt collector , even if there are scant funds in the account on the day the levy is imposed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Explain how assessing a 125 dollar bank levy fee when an account has 50 dollars in it helps resolve the ongoing debt resolution.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The Debt collector gets nothing and the customer is hit with a 125 dollar bank levy fee.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Why isn't there a 100 dollar float that is impervious to a bank levy fee and protected from the debt collector's clutches as well?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Once again, we get back to the same underpinning, Judges who simply decide on whether a default has occurred without caring why the default occurred are basically rubber stamping minions of a system corrupted by a lack of fairness.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "People can lose income based on circumstances beyond their control, yet the system doesn't even blanche an eye.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "A debtor who purposely runs up debt quickly and defaults is treated identically to someone who had a perfect payment history but had to stop working to become a CareGiver for a family member.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "A debtor who purposely runs up debt quickly and hires a lawyer can strategically default and possibly get a better resolution than an honest person with an impeccable payment history who has lost income because of an event beyond their control.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "837", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think they should have to have a license to be debt collectors", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and at the time they did not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally there should be harassment laws regarding just this matter about landlords", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "as if someone sues you 3Xs for the same thing, they should lose their collections license.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I even responded from the very beginning with a certified letter stating that I did not owe any part of the debt!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Additionally what did help after almost 20 years was reporting the landlords real estate license for violating business practices in NYS for overcharging rent statements.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "This certainly got their attention ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "however I still had to retain an attorney for a lawsuit against them and prevailed ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "but then you have to pay the 20% of what you recoup to the attorney.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "I wish they would just lose their license for harassing you for 20 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "It is disgusting that no one in NYC has done anything about it", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "but then I don't need to tell you how corrupt everyone there is and that includes the legal system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "NYC government and housing system is like dealing with the mob", "reasons": ["13"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I say that after having to deal with them aggressively for the past 3 years after being attacked for almost 20", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "796", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "No matter how you slice this conversation, phone calls are the biggest abuse.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "You can have rules and do about the time,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "but they are ignored.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Until you or the FTC creates rules that fine these people -- and not put the burden on the consumer to sue -- this abuse will go on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I have to laugh at these querstions.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "You have to be putting me on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The most abusive things debt collectors do are with their phones.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "They block their numbers still.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "They use various numbers", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "they mislead their identities.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "THE PROBLEM is the onus is on the hapless consumer to get legal redress.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Not good enough.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "You need to create fines and actually impose them.", "reasons": ["13"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "That will stop this phone abuse.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "fact", "text": "They call at work, always wkill have some excuse.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "fact", "text": "and call after hours.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "Be honest, this is an outrage what these companies have done, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "and nobody has minded the store on them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "policy", "text": "Never should the onus be on the consumer to get this to stop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "policy", "text": "You have to find a lawyer who thinks a whopping $1,000 is worth suing over.", "reasons": ["18"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "You have rigged this system in favor of the sharks.,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "value", "text": "and that is why these sleazy companies have proliferated and have grown more and more egregious in their actions.", "reasons": ["20"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "policy", "text": "no more recorded calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "policy", "text": "call from one number", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "policy", "text": "as soon as someone says stop calling, STOP.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 25, "type": "policy", "text": "if there is any call beyond that, they get fined.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 26, "type": "value", "text": "Agreed, people will have to write a letter ", "reasons": ["27"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 27, "type": "value", "text": "because none of these companies will admit they were told to stop calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 28, "type": "value", "text": "But they do receive the letters,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 29, "type": "policy", "text": "which should go to a physical address and to a person, not just a vague company name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 30, "type": "policy", "text": "Last, stop allowing these bad companies to change their names.", "reasons": ["31"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 31, "type": "value", "text": "They get in trouble, they change their names, and go on doing terrible things under another name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 32, "type": "policy", "text": "Just look online at some of these companies and how many names they've gone through.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 33, "type": "value", "text": "The reason this got so bad is nobody has been looking out for the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1126", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "While Alternative 1 seems simplest,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "there are hidden complications.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Who defines what \"principal\" means?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "With revolving credit accounts, interest accrues (as finance charges) and is rolled into the balance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "So does \"principal\" mean only the part of the balance that was charged by the cardholder (very difficult, if not impossible, for a collector to calculate) or the total charged off amount?", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I understand that it can be difficult when dealing with different kinds of debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "But I don't think this option will work for a large portion of consumer debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Alternative 2 doesn't work", "reasons": ["11", "8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "because who defines when a consumer \"defaults\" on an account?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Many of us have missed a payment here or there,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "but we get back on track.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "So it's too ambiguous.", "reasons": ["9_10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "That leaves Alternative 3 as the most feasible,", "reasons": ["6", "7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "but what about accounts that never had a periodic statement or billing statement?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "I propose breaking down the total amount by stating the amount owed on the last statement issued by the original creditor, or, if no statement was ever issued, the original amount of the debt when incurred, and then an itemization of all debits and credits applied since that balance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "378", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Only one collection call since I changed my phone listing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "No debt collector has ever admitted to me that they got my number out of the phone book.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1166", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had surgery at a hospital in 2006.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have 2 forms of insurance, both excellent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Therefore I rarely have a medical bill to pay, or it is for a very small amount.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Sometime after the surgery (I do not recall how long after the procedure), there were repeated calls to my phone by an actual person who said, \" This is (first name), give me a call at (phone number)\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Since we did not know the person,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "no one called back.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "We thought we should report it to the DONOTCALL list,", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "but we had no company name to report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "Finally I happened to answer the phone when that number appeared and the male voice said, \"you know what this is about, right?\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I said, \"no\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "He said, \" you have an overdue charge with (hospital name). You haven't paid your bill. I work with a bill collection company\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "I said \"I have never received a bill.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "He said \"really?\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "I said , \"yes\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "He said, \"Call accounting at the hospital\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "I called the hospital and they said to talk to my insurance company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "I called my 2nd insurance company and they said both the first and the second insurance company had paid the hospital.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "The 2nd insurance company said I did owe money on the bill, something like $1.08.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "A bill collection company had been hired to collect $1.08 for which I had never received a bill!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "I asked both insurance companies to send me additional copies of the Explanation of Benefits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I received the copies, I sent them to the billing department of the hospital with a check for the amount that the 2nd insurance company said I owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "testimony", "text": "I never did receive a bill.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "testimony", "text": "Nor was i warned it might go to a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "testimony", "text": "A collection agency was hired for an amount just slightly over $1.00.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "value", "text": "Because of this experience, I do not plan ever to use this hospital again if I can help it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 25, "type": "testimony", "text": "My family has had referrals to doctors associated with this hospital,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 26, "type": "value", "text": "but I always try to get a doctor who is not associated with it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "845", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Most consumers have a bad taste in their mouth from the way that a select few agencies used to operate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "And rightfully so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "But look at it from the other side.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If i owed you $1,000 debt do you really think sending me a letter would do the trick?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Would you attempt to call me to find out my intentions?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "My point is, agencies are operating under a pretty broad microscope.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Compliance with the laws is being monitored very closely now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "We view ourselves at my company as extensions of customer service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "If we call you, we specifically ask if we are calling a cell and if it is okay to reach you on that number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "If you say no, we remove the number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "204", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The FDCPA contains an exception for creditors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should include in any rule confirmation that the same practices prohibited for collectors under the FDCPA would be unfair, deceptive, or abusive acts and practices if done by a creditor.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "349", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should be aware of who is handling collection procedures.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The seller of any consumer debt should be required to notify the debtor of which debt owed to which creditor, is being sold by xyz organization to 123 debt collector.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The effective date of the debt sale and contact info for the new collector should be included.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1013", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I recommend that the option to bring a suit in the jurisdiction where the consumer signed the contract should be removed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "In many situations, consumers may not actually sign a contract (e.g. credit cards),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "they may sign an agreement in a distant location (for medical payment at a hospital on vacation), ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "or they may have moved in the years since opening the account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I believe the most consumer-friendly option is to file suit where the consumer resides at time of commencement (unless it concerns real property and then it should be where the property is located).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "With respect to geographic size concerns, it is important to note that many states are facing budget crises that affect the civil divisions of state courts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "In one of our largest districts, our options for filing suit was reduced from 32 courts down to 2.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "If there is a concern for protecting consumers in this particular area, I recommend a section of the rule that prohibits collections from choosing a court venue with the intention of interfering with the consumer's ability to participate in the action.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "To prove a violation, the consumer (or regulatory agency) would need to demonstrate that the collector had no reason to file suit in that court other than burdening the consumer (thus demonstrating intent).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "538", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "People get fired for personal calls at work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["1_2"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I worked at a place where employee phone call was recorded and randomly monitored due to the sensitivity of our work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "And every now and then an employee would get caught making/taking a personal phone call and would be fired with no questions asked.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Work is not the place for personal business.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1073", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think the current limits are fine.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The MA rules are too restrictive and frankly could be a disservice to the consumer who wants to try to resolve the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I do not believe in robo calling but do believe that preview dialing on an automated dialer system should not be prohibited ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "as the agent still has to review the information on the account and push a button to allow the dial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "995", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I too, do not answer calls with no name, no number or 800 numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "After over a year of unemployment and only able to get part time work, I had to give up my landline.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I get repeated unknown calls on my cell, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "even though all creditors were sent written notices not to contact my cell number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I'm almost at a point that I cannot afford my cell,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "but if it give it up I have no way to get contact from a potential employer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "When I get a full time job I will gladly pay my debts,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "but constant calls will not get the debt paid any faster.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "Not one company called me to give the the credit,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "so they should not call my cell and cost me more money that will prolong them getting paid.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "Besides, most of the calls are robo-calls with no message ever being left ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "so I never know who the call is for.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1231", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree with MER.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have experience as a debtor, pro-bono attorney and debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "You can't expect collectors to be judge or jury.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The cease communication right is meant to to force the collector to sue or go away.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1127", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The case law related to this portion of the FDCPA has made it risky for collectors to include anything other than exactly what the FDCPA says.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "However, I don't think the law, as written, is easy to understand.", "reasons": ["2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "For example - the first sentence says unless you dispute the debt, it will be considered valid (\"dispute\" and \"valid\" aren't defined), but then goes on to say what the creditor will do if you notify them in writing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "So if the consumer only disputes verbally, what rights do they have, if any?", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "I think the law should be clarified,", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "and then I think the CFPB should create a uniform \"Summary of Consumer Rights\" that can be required to be included with all initial letters from collectors.", "reasons": ["6", "7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "That way, debt collectors don't have to worry about overshadowing and trying to fit everything onto one page, or with the tricky area of providing legal advice by interpreting the FDCPA for the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Also, consumers can get a consistent message from all collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "If there is a concern about it being separate from the initial letter from the collector, there can be a mandatory one-line disclosure providing a link to a CFPB website with that Summary of Consumer Rights.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "891", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I think that the CFPB should come up with a regulation that prohibits a creditor, and a debt collector, from sending the debt for collection to another debt collection company AFTER a consumer disputes the debt, or sends a \"cease and desist\" letter to the debt collection agency.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In my cases that I worked on, a \"cease and desist\" letter was sent to both the debt collector and original creditor requesting that they cease collecting the debt as per the FDCPA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "However, all they do is close out one debt collection company and send the account to another one.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Then the consumer has to repeat the process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should come up with a regulation that states once the debt is disputed or a \"cease and desist\" letter is sent to the debt collector, THAT debt collector must advise the original creditor that a C&D letter was sent.", "reasons": ["0", "1_3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1309", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have experience collection companies who buys the debt from the 1st 2nd or 3rd party add on its fees along with the other companies fees,then submit a new account number to the original account as though it was a new account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "So, a original account for the sake of argument was $500.00 turns out to be listed on your credit report as a $3,000 delinquent account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Government laws should not allow this practice to exist.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "What ever the original account is that's what should be reported not interest and additional fees a collection company deems it can add to your credit bureau report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1250", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Texting should follow all rules regarding phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Email should follow rules set in place regarding written, mailed, letters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "744", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think your idea is an excellent one.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "My concern is that it might force interest rates even higher.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Ideally, there would probably be less overall defaults if consumers, when first getting credit were required to pay at least 5% of the total due each and every month.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "840", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree with anoymousme,", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am constantly called up to 5 times a day by numerous collectors for my kids bills.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Why should we have to bothered.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I gave my kids the message ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "but they ignore it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "They do not have a land line ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "so they call me!!!On NEWYEARS ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am dropping my land line which I have had for 40 years just to be rid of these pests!", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "How long are parents responsible for deadbeat children.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "502", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think that we are discussing how to block a collector from calling you.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "You shouldn't have to feel that you have to \" block \" a call .", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "You should just answer and ask them not to call you.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1180", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "States Rights versus Federal Rights are the biggest issues with the rule making process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There is a vast divergence of state law requirements that create areas that confuse consumers, regulators, and those in the industry as to what laws apply in what settings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "A universal rule that would apply in all settings would assist all parties to remove the ambiguity and conflict that currently exists with state multiple levels of regulation at the municipal, state, and two regulators at the federal level", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "320", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Would like to see regulators approve email as a method of delivery for notifications.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Most people keep their email even when they change physical addresses.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Harder on the post office", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but probably much more effective, with no-cost proof of attempted contact.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "622", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It would be a good idea to create a national database of collectors and assign them an ID number just like the IRS.", "reasons": ["2", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Require them to state their name and ID number just like IRS employees do.", "reasons": ["0", "2", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This would allow debtors to easily identify an abusive collector or just call a debt collection agency and ask to speak to a specific employee.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "If they call and leave a voicemail they are required to state their ID number somewhere in the recording.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It would be good for both debtors and collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "882", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I recently discovered that my mortgage company does not have the note on my mortgage ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and they can not locate the note.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I am current and have no concerns on reducing the payment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have asked the mortgage holder what should we do.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "For the last 8 months they have sent us notices saying they are researching the issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "523", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Once I tell a debt collector I am a unpaid CareGiver", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and that is why I had to stop making payments,", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "In essence they were telling me to let my parents die if necessary and go get a job.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was repeatedly baited with the comment, \"So you are a \"refuse to pay\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I found this type of conduct outside the lines of common decency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had a business,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had to give up the business to become an unpaid CareGiver.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "If I had been shown at the time I apparently agreed to the credit card agreement that there truly were no ifs ands or buts in regards to monthly payments forgiveness on an \"unsecured\" debt, I would have come up with a different business model that did not require credit card debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Credit card companies get to present themselves as pro family in their advertising when the exact opposite is true in times of crisis.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "Ask people who had a dramatic life changing incident occur how the credit card companies treated them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "Ask the Colorado flood victims, or the Hurricane Sandy Victims, or the person who was the victim of a hit and run how the credit card companies treated them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "These are the same credit card companies that lobbied the comptroller of the currency in 2002 to keep their monopoly on credit card debt suspension insurance and the outrageous overpriced premiums they were charging their customers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "One of the best ways consumers had to be responsible regarding their credit card debts was having AFFORDABLE credit card debt suspension insurance.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "fact", "text": "This option was stolen from consumers in 2002 when the comptroller of the currency allowed credit card companies to over charge by 1000% to 2000% on monthly credit card debt suspension insurance premiums.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "I created a time line document that shows how the financial elite stole fairness from the people in regards to credit card products.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["15"]}, {"id": 15, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://debtsuspensionrights.blogspot.com/2013/05/my-consumer-financial-protection-bureau.html\">My appearance in front of the CFPB in May of 2013 and the research I shared with them.</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "483", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Check your state law, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "such as Illinois has its own Collection Agency Act.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "It's a licensed profession and Atty general for the state would be a start for a complaint.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.ilga.gov/legislation/ilcs/ilcs3.asp?ActID=1355&ChapterID=24", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "601", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree with Bonzarel.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The obvious solution is to ban debt collection calls to cell phones, period.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Not everybody has the same options on their mobile plans, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and some have strict time/call/texting limits and/or restrictions.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "493", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I knew a man who was sued by a debt collector and he was not served.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "\"Someone\" was served, but not at his address and he was denied due process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "He learned of the suit when it was a judgment on his credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "He attempted to have the judgment overturned for lack of due process and the judge would not grant it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Unfortunate, but yes they are allowed to deny due process and get away with it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1190", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "As medical records become more digitized, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I see no significant cost increase to debt collectors in passing on substantive info to debtors,", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "although debt collectors are bound to say otherwise.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "My concern is that the cost to consumers of inadequate information is routinely underestimated or dismissed as trivial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["4_8"]}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I worked with a non-profit in Alabama, I took part in an informational meeting on a program of federal assistance (Farmers Home Admin, IIRC) in securing access to home loans on affordable terms for low-income workers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "One woman who was at the meeting spoke of having been denied access to the program because of a single blot on her credit record, namely an unpaid medical bill.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "She said she had not paid it because she could not determine what the charges were for, was unaware of any medical treatment she had not paid for, and could not get a straight answer from the debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "She decided the debt might be illegitimate and refused to pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a result she was excluded from access to a home loan.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "This is an example of a consumer on a limited income who was consistently disciplined about her finances and who should have had access to credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I find it significant that it was a medical bill that tripped her up, placing her in a category in which even the FHA would not work with her.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "From this point, credit was only available to her at high cost if at all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "I am confident that the rule I am suggesting would have led her to either pay the debt or dispute it formally on the basis of valid information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "What it would not have done is to leave her to conclude that she was being scammed and refuse to pay at all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "This anecdote (and I admit I only have anecdotal evidence) does suggest that legitimate credit agencies also stand to benefit by disclosing information that will persuade skeptical consumers that they do actually owe the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "381", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The agency needs to be careful of new rules that will, though unintended, be harmful to the free market.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "However, it is important that litigation is monitored to ensure that the system does not allow reward with no risk.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "A plaintiff in a lawsuit cannot be placed in a situation where it is rewarding to sue with insufficient cause and minimal risk.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Creditors and those following in the process of recovery do not need additional regulation in this area", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "since their efforts are monitored by the CFPB.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The CFPB does not need to set standards for the industry,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "but make it clear that only those documents provided to the court in the original filing will be considered in a CFPB review.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "If in the course of a CFPB review, it is found that litigation was filed without a successful verification of the facts, the CFPB could award the amount sought by the filing to the defendant of the case and a fine to the CFPB of no less than $2,000 but no more than the amount sought.", "reasons": ["8", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "This position would motivate the litigant to ensure their facts were correct before any filing took place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "This position would allow CFPB to review cases filed no matter how they were adjudicated by the involved court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "This review could be conducted at CFPB offices", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "since it only requires the original filings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "This review could be initiated simply based on a complaint to the agency's offices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "The penalty could be adjustable based on a variety of agency standards.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "I would have to take more time to consider when the plaintiff was not the original creditor or a member of the recovery industry,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "but, again, there must be a risk associated with the reward to stop nuisance suits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1088", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The current validation notice is already too long--bordering on \"boilerplate\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "To add more language to this would confuse or intimidate the least sophisticated debtor and/or lead them to immediately ask that the creditor cease communication.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The problem with that strategy is that it forces the creditor to file suit, thereby incurring court costs that will be added to the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Instead, debtors should be encouraged to communicate their questions & concerns to the collector who can then (after right-party verification) openly discuss the account & quite possibly answer the debtor's question(s).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "382", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There needs to be something in place to stop the frivilous law suits that agencies have to spend thousands of dollars to defend even though they have tried to explain to the consumers / attorneys that there was no wrong doing and no case", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "a lot of these consumers file the suits Pro Se and continue pushing for a settlement or trial", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "in these cases the agencies spend monies to prove there was no cause for action to begin with and to have a judge agree with the agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Please look at putting some kind of penalty on consumers or their attorneys when they send settlement demands or file law suits when they have been shown that there is / was no case", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "626", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Creditors should only be allowed to call between the hours of 9am until 7pm local time unless they have written consent (maybe even a web form) that gives them a minimum 3 hour window in which to call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, they are limited to 3 phone calls a day maximum.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1128", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This proposed rulemaking is not about credit reporting.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I understand that people have significant concerns about their credit reports.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "But that belongs in a reform of the Fair Credit Reporting Act, not the FDCPA.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Inserting credit reporting rules into the FDCPA would make things difficult for debt collectors who don't report to credit reporting agencies at all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1186", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a charged off loan which I have been trying to get a repay plan on", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "but the debt is listed as one amount on my CBR and the debt collector had the balance increased by $12K more when discussing it over the phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "That is outrageous that they do not have an accurate amount of what is owed to the original lender.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "224", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "No, it is not even clear who a debt collector is, particularly under CA law.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The person sending the validating notice is typically a debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This just causes confusion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1063", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "These so-called \"Blue Laws\" that prohibit cars lots being opened on Sundays and liquor being sold on Sundays, requiring the debt collection industry from closing down on Sundays (no calls, no letters, no contact) would not create any undo burden ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "as many other regulated industries (car, liquor, gambling, etc) already abide to such \"blue laws\" and they operate just fine and make plenty of profits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The debt collection industry should be required to close down completely on Sundays.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1327", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Just like Cable companies may expect their customers to give them a four hour window for service calls,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "consumers should be allowed to choose a time frame they prefer to be called within.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "If they never respond within that time frame, then the debt collector could try a different time frame.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "423", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "More information to the consumer with the initial notification would be more confusing and intimidating than it already is for them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Simplifying the initial notification while including information about how to contact someone if you do not recognized this obligation is the way to go.", "reasons": ["0", "2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Then the CFPB can design and require everyone to send a separate Summary of Consumer Rights to a consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It could also be available in the exact same form on the CFPB website and on informed professionals websites within the industry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I would maintain the consumer's right to ask for a cease communication,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "but I would suggest that the CFPB would serve everyone better by including that the CFPB would suggest that the consumer may be better served by keeping this communication available except as a last resort.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This solution also bears the added advantage of making sure the public is aware of the assistance available through the CFPB.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "909", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is precisely what lead to my filing bankruptcy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Debt buying and selling, made a debt that was 10 years old, reappear on my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Each time I mentioned that the debt was time-barred.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was informed that the debt had been bought, and that the \"clock\" had been restarted.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "720", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The most important would be not to call at work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "That's really the most important to the collectors, too,", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "because a person out of work isn't likely to pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1272", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "A question that I'd ask surrounds dialects.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "There are numerous dialects for Spanish, French, etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and it would be very expensive for agencies to translate every letter into every dialect of a certain language, Spanish being the most common for this type of occurrence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I'd greatly appreciate feedback, commentary and also recommendations on everyone's view on how to address differing language formalities.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1226", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As an \"authorized user\" who has no access to the actual credit card, my credit rating is suffering ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "because the \"account holder\" presently, is only able to make the minimum monthly payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think this is fair and have not been able to get a direct response from anyone to see if card companies can legally do this when they collected no information from me but my name!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "There was NO FULL DISCLOSURE stating that as only being an \"authorized user\" said card company would report on my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "682", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I see what you mean,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but that tiny percentage suffers incredible annoyance and harassment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Should they pay what they don't owe, merely to get out from under?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "All we've ever asked for is an itemized bill from the original creditor,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but the collectors act as if that's too much.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "And they say--and probably believe--that we've received other bills, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "but we haven't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "We've lived in the same place for 30 years", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "how awful it must be for people who move a lot.", "reasons": ["5_7"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "610", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Any collector who uses a robocall, without first having a live person call to verify that the phone number is correct, is lazy and irresponsible.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Aside from being a major nuisance, robocalls to a third party are always an improper disclosure ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "because prerecorded calls are required to include the name of the company at the start of the message (per the TCPA).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've received dozens and dozens of calls like this, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and now I know which of my neighbors are alleged to owe money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I say \"alleged\", ", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "because the companies making these calls are usually the same scofflaws who have been sued repeatedly for trying to collect nonexistent debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Outlawing robocalls, particularly robocalls to third parties, would hurt the bad actors without having much impact on legitimate collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I wouldn't have a problem with live callers using autodialers, except that the technology used by some collection agencies is so far behind the times.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Telemarketers are able to stay within the required 3% abandonment rate,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "yet my experience is that the drop rate on live calls from collectors ranges from 50% to 100%.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "Yes, I had one company hang up immediately every single time one of their agents called me. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "I'm not sure how this is profitable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "Extending the FTC's 3% rule to debt collection calls would address this issue.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "680", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "You know, my only experience is with medical debts,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "but with those, we have NOT been notified several times, or sometimes, even one time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "No one seems to care if the address is right", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and when you're dealing with an old person, the billing address is often not the same as the physical address);", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "sometimes the bill seems to go to what they claim is a collection agency even before the insurance company finishes with it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "We are perfectly happy to pay our bills,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "but our contract is with the provider,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "and that's who we pay, not a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "521", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "That's business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Debt collectors--small, medium, and large--know the cost of doing business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "And if they don't know, then they need to find a new \"career.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1297", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As Director I can clearly in good faith state that as we service our potential losses ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and my Team make collection calls contact is generally made at work place as well.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Let me also state that many of the call backs are made from Members at work as well.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It all depends on the employer and the work conditions surrounding the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "484", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "At least in Illinois there is a Caller ID spoofing law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["2"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Still get calls every day with false/unintelligible called ID listed and no message left.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.ilga.gov/legislation/ilcs/ilcs3.asp?ActID=2925&ChapterID=67", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "416", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I strongly endore drose977's response.", "reasons": ["1_3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Currently, debt collection agencies can sell debt without proper validation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Or they can sell the debt if a consumer disputes the debt and the agency can't product the proper validation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "These things should not be allowed and are very detrimental to the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should be protected above collectors and other agencies", "reasons": ["5", "6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "as they, typically, have far less resources to fight inaccurate information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Additionally, the inaccurate information adversely effects consumers more than any other group in these situations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should not be allowed to report a debt as 30 days late if the debt isn't 30 days late.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "The law should include stiff enforcable penalities to deter collectors from pre-dating debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "These rules should apply for any debt reported late at any time, not just the first 30 days.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1314", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Debt was sold to another company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "So now debt is listed on my credit twice.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "So debt will last more than 10 years on report.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Plus I've been a victim of identity theft twice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Both times I reported it to the police and to the credit agencies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Unfortunately nothing police can do but write a report for proof.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Credit agency was ordered to put a fraud alert on my social but fail to do so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1031", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is entirely too much information to require.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It's not the job of creditors or collectors to send notices about \"best practices\" or personnel information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This thread is about notice that a debt is assigned to collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "NOT sold, but simply outsourced to someone who specializes in collecting past due debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Notices is given when the validation notice is sent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The company who sends it is the collector;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "the letter itself will state the name of the creditor to whom the debt is owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "That's enough.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "698", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am an experienced recipient of collection calls.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "As I have explained in another post here, I live in a fairly large metro area,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and whenever anyone with my very common last name and first initial skips town without paying his/her bills, I'm the one who gets the calls from the debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I know that a call about \"an important business matter,\" is a call about a debt.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have received many of these kinds of calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Whenever a debt collector calls me and leaves a message without a name, it doesn't take me very long to figure out that the call is from a debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "If the debt collector calls and leaves a name, that debt collector is revealing to me, an unrelated third party, that the individual has a debt in collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I consider this to be a violation of the spirit of the FDCPA if not the letter.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Whenever a debt collector calls me, I am burdened with the knowledge that I now know the name of someone else who has a debt in collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've gotten any number of the calls described in #4 telling me not to listen if I'm not the named individual.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "The big problem with that is that, one again, the name of a debtor is being revealed to me,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "and then there's the added dilemma of the fact that now my phone number has been programmed into a debt collector's robo dialer.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "When that happens, the calls continue to come.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "I always disobey the instructions and listen to the message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "I then call the debt collector to report a case of mistaken identity.", "reasons": ["15"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "It's the only way to stop the calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "In all the collection calls I have gotten over the years, I have received only one message with the \"mini-Miranda\" warning.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I called the debt collector to report another case of mistaken identity I was connected with an individual in a call center in India.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "After I told the woman she had the wrong person, I thanked her for the \"mini-Miranda\" and she hung up on me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "value", "text": "I don't have any answers, just lots of experience.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "I hope someone finds this information useful.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "902", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Your point is understandable;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "however the statement you referred to is known as the mini-Miranda.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "This statement is a requirement in a debt collector's initial communication", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and in some states every communication).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Typically, the validation verbiage is included in a sheet of it's own with several other disclosures a debt collector is required to provide.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "As far as law being slanted against the consumer, I would disagree.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The laws surrounding contacting consumers and the information required to be given is quite stringent,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "the problem is the channels which are directly regulated by the law are outdated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "The primary law that regulates a debt collector was written in the 70's and did not directly define that is thrown around all too often, harassment (among others).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Because of this, if a debt collector sends a letter and makes a phone call, he may very well be held accountable in a court of law for \"harassment\".", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "Most collectors settle out of court", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "as defending a suit as frivolous as the one described above would cost much more than settling with a consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1157", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Currently, CRA's deny responsibility for \"reporting\" inaccurate information given to them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "CRA's should be liable for both actual and punitive damages caused by \"reporting\" inaccurate information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "444", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "First parties should still have the right to sue if they deem it necessary.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I have no problem with this rule if it is directed to third party debt buyers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1067", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I'm in the same situation--get calls about numerous people with my last name and one or the other of my two initials.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "None of the people being sought are even related to me, as far as I know, much less living with me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I would like to be able to make an official declaration that I have no delinquent debt and that I do not live with anyone who does.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I'd be willing to renew the declaration once a year in order to stop receiving these calls that are nothing more than fishing expeditions.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "572", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "The first entity I will probably take to small claims court and possibly file a complaint with Kamala Harris.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "The second incident I started sending faxes messages in big bold letters to the same fax where my prior faxes had been lost, asking other workers to look to see if they had taken the papers by accident.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I also faxed overnight warning those who might have access to that room that taking fax documents could lead to their arrest.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I did this for several days in a row.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was the only way I could think of to apply a much needed enema to those who have established a routine and can't shake free from it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Of course this assumes that they care.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "908", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "There are requirements for validating a debt to the customer set in the FDCPA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "There are investigation requirements in other aspects of federal law when a consumer disputes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "A debt cannot simply be created out of thin air.", "reasons": ["0", "1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Agencies who engage in this sort of practice are usually stopped relatively quickly and fined quite heavily (as well as subjected to cease and desist and regulatory action).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The fact is, while a debt collector is required to maintain certain pieces of information and validate certain pieces of information, the consumer is not required to do anything further than say, \"I don't owe this\" to make collections stop for a period of time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Just like for debt collectors, the few that do it wrong ruin if for the many that do it right,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "consumers in my opinion should be required to furnish some sort of support of dispute.", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "846", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Every validation notice should include, not only the name, but the address and phone number of the current owner of the debt.", "reasons": ["1", "6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "It is not always the case that the consumer knows who the owner of the debt is, or how to contact them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This would not be a burden on collection agencies,", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "because it would only require the collection agency to cut and paste the address and phone number of the debt owner onto the validation notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The collection agency should already have this information in their company records,", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "as the debt collector is forwarding consumer payments to said debt owner's address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This would allow the consumer to attempt to deal with the debt owner directly to try to resolve the dispute.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "For example, a case of mistaken identity can more easily be resolved by talking to a customer service representative of the debt owner, than by talking to a debt collector.", "reasons": ["8_9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "The debt collector has no authority to correct the mistake,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "but a customer service representative of the debt owner does.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "595", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "To the first question, due diligence is a must.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Even if collectors are allowed to continue litigation (which I do not see going away,) there must be a penalty for the collector if false claim is made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "If a collector starts litigation and it is found to be against the wrong person, compensation and additional penalty should be paid by the entity initiating the litigation in the form of a reasonable fee to the victim and an additional (and substantial) fee to the governing authority to help cover oversight expenses.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "To the second question, I believe an overwhelmingly large portion of consumer debt can be repaid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "However, there are always going to be exceptions to this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "In cases where debt can not be collected for whatever reason, it should be written off as truly not collectable and no not be allow to be sold again as debt to be collected.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Fine tuning and definitions of \"Not Collectable\" will have to be worked out by the appropriate oversight bureau or agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "To the third question, both party's must be measured.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "There are currently established credit reporting agencies to monitor the consumer side of this issue and an additional, numerical evaluation score can be added to the consumer's already established credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "That would be a starting point that can be expanded on as the system is fine tuned.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "The collector, on the other hand, would require a new measuring system that would not only score the company as a whole, but the individuals taking part in any debt resolution activities.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "For successful examples of such a system I would direct you to the Department of Transportation, Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration and their Compliance-Safety-Accountability system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Admittedly, their system is much more complex and dives much deeper than would be required for the debt industry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "However, their point system is valid and flexible for future change.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "It would also allow for measurement of the initial creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "Such measurement would give the government and investors a better idea of a given business' risk level.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "Add to this mix, the recommendations from Mr. Bartmann and you have a system whereby collectors and financial institutions will better regulate themselves to achieve an ethical and responsible outcome and not hide behind the \"what I did was legal\" defense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "It would be a Win-Win for both sides and bring many consumers out of the debt death spiral.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "Lastly, the federal government could implement this system with a minimal impact on state autonomy.", "reasons": ["19"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "value", "text": "It would reduce the number of litigation in state and local courts, thereby motivating the states to take part.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "635", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "How about allowing arbitrators to not be bound entirely by the law, but also by common sense when it comes credit card defaults?", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Common sense tells us that if a Colorado flood washes away a community, those in the community are possibly not going to be able to pay their credit card bills for a few months.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Common sense tells us that a medical emergency, being the victim of a hit and run accident, destruction of a home, or becoming an unpaid CareGiver for a family member should take precedence over the monthly payment requirement. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This is not about debt forgiveness, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "its about declaring a debt neutral, no more penalties, fees or interest rate charges are applied to the debt, and the debtor agrees to pay off the debt in a reasonable manner, even if it takes 10 years to do so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.change.org/petitions/congress-create-debt-neutrality-rights-for-paying-down-credit-cards-student-loans", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "890", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have had my cell phone number for 4 1/2 years;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "the previous owner of my number had a student loan debt....", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I cannot get collection agencies to stop calling me!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Every time I emphatically tell them I'm not the person in question ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and the person dutifully \"takes me off the list\".", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "But in another few months I hear from them (or probably a collector who bought the list) all over again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I'm familiar with the FDCPA,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "but I don't think it currently provides a practical solution for me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1123", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "But they also can't send you a signed paper for something you agreed to online, or over the phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "So few people actually put a pen to paper these days to sign a formal written agreement.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "So that's an unfair requirement when it doesn't always exist.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "340", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Blocking caller ID information is disingenuous to say the least.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Most consumers won't respond to blocked numbers or ID's anyway.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should be required to identify themselves and to provide caller ID information that identifies them.", "reasons": ["0", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Most people who cannot pay their bills are aware of the problem,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "so being reminded under false pretenses is more of an annoyance than a solution to the problem.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "341", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I'm with Massachusetts on this one.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Repetitive and robo-calls are annoying and not productive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Another fact about robo-calls is that their messages often start in the middle,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "or maybe this is done on purpose.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "When it has happened to me, I just hang up.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Policies regulating the number of contacts made within a specific time period should include all modes of technology.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "527", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I often find that some banks wont allow their agencies to take debit or credit card.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "All agencies should accept debit and credit payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Its like they are stuck in 1950.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "339", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Most landlines and cell phones have caller ID technology ;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "if the number comes up showing a toll-free number or an unknown caller, many consumers will let such calls go to voice mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Voice mail messages need to be discreet.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "No one needs their kids hearing messages from debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Anyone returning a call regarding a voice mail message should be informed by a live customer service rep of the mini Miranda warning.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "This should be done only after the person returning the call to the collector verifies his or her identity as the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "407", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If a consumer sends a post dated check(s) and it bounces then it may not fall under the bad check enforcement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Also, consumers use ACH capability to repay a debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "so if the amount is not available, then this may also not fall under bad check enforcement.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "My experience is more consumers use ACH rather than personal check distribution.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "there are numerous reasons why checks bounce", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "so I suggest a look see as to determining the reason or cause why the check bounced.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1025", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This option doesn't make economic sense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Debt buyers do serve a practical purpose ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "because they allow the creditor to unload a massive amount of debt at one time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The cost of negotiating individual deals with each of those 1 million delinquent consumers would negate the benefit they get from the consolidated offload.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Debt buyers allow the creditors to clear their books, which enables the cycle of lending to continue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "The transaction between those two entities doesn't change what is actually owed on the account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "450", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Can there be a national repository to report abusive phone calls from debt collectors that masked (fake and \"spoof\") their caller ID?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I got a brand new phone number a few years ago ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and it obviously previously belonged to someone who is delinquent on their bills ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I get calls everyday from debt collectors looking for the person who had my phone number before me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "No matter how many times I tell them they have the wrong number, they don't care and they just keep calling and they call from spoofed phone numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "And this is my cell phone, which is against the law for debt collectors to call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "The same debt collectors call with faked caller IDs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "Here are just some of the phone numbers these debt collectors use: 808-792-8186 462643 858-568-7632 805-322-4584 706-913-1192 808-348-0083 858-345-4076 858-312-7724 908-505-9008 800-633-2677 252-808-7969 571-522-0386 407-712-3093 213-816-2972 804-721-3193 678-781-4530 427307 858-240-4079", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1237", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "My experience has been that people younger than I (a boomer) prefer to communicate electronically (emails, texts & chats).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I know that when I was deeply in debt, I would have preferred not to have to speak to a real person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "There is a legitimate concern about unencrypted email or the potential for consumers not to consider that others may have access to their email.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "However, in general, we should encourage communication, however that happens - especially if it is in a form preferred by a particular consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "I believe that emails, chats & texts should all be considered writings.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I don't know how you include all disclosures unless you direct someone to a place where they can read them in plain english.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "862", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "What I had in mind when I made this comment was that some debtors are in debt because of a medical condition that has negatively impacted their ability to work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "They may be on Social Security disability for this reason.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Sometimes, that medical condition is scientifically known to be aggravated by stress, such as any heart condition, or an anxiety disorder.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Currently, Section 806 of the FDCPA makes abuse or harassment of debtors illegal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "However, what qualifies as abuse might be different for a debtor with a disabling medical condition that is sensitive to stress.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "My hope, and my suggestion, is that there could be some way for debtors to make collection agencies aware of the fact that the debtor has a documented medical disability, and that abusive or harassing phone calls have additional health consequences for the debtor.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1375", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "While I do not advocate daily robo-calling, I have to wonder why a consumer finds themselves on the receiving end of these calls?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Receiving the daily call would indicate the consumer is also continually ignoring this debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Sadly, there is a demographic that thinks this way.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If the consumer has found themselves in a tough spot I would think they would choose to take the call or contact the debt collecting entity to try to remedy the situation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "As far as regulations I do believe that one call a week is sufficient.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The idea of the robo-call is to keep the debt on the consumers mind in an effort that when they get the money they will remember to call and pay the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Any other purpose I think would be considered an attempt to annoy the consumer into paying.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "The demographic that allows this is never going to pay anyway ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "so why play the game.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Even a robo-call costs money ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "so why continually throw good money after bad.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "In 30 years of this business I realize there are two types of people, the one's who want to pay their bill and the ones who never intended to pay in the first place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "645", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "I would have to point out that there is many complaints in regards to how abusive or harassing debt collectors are according to consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a third-party debt collector, I receive dozens harassment complaints daily.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I would just like to note that 80% of the time, these consumers that my fellow co-workers and I come across, are complaining of harassment and abuse;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and 100% of them are truly just unwilling to face the facts.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "That's what they are complaining about.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "When we tell them that they owe a debt, they consider it harassment and abuse.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "They just don't want to hear their problems.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, grant it, there are some debt collectors that are harassing and abusive, but the other 98% are just pointing out the truth.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "When consumers realize that it is them and not us, debt collectors would receive a better reputation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "But until then, we are the enemy in the consumer's eyes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "817", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If you want to instantly level the playing field, make any credit card debt above and beyond the moment of default, disputable.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Disputability of any amount over the amount at the moment of default would instantly get both the credit card companies and the debt collectors working with the consumer on a reasonable plan going forward, no?", "reasons": ["2_4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "As it stands now, credit card companies can and usually do jump the interest rate up to as high as 29.9%", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and may even let the account stay in default ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "as they rack up frequent default points on the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I gave up my regional emmy award winning video business to become a caregiver for both of my parents, eventually savings ran out and I notified each of my credit card vendors ahead of any default.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "NONE could offer me anything other than, \"pay your bill on time\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "If instead the credit card companies know that once the default occurs they cannot accrue any more penalties, fees or interest rate charges on the debt, they will bend over backwards to work with the alleged defaulter to get them to pay down the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "Citibank rate jacked my never late payment 15 year old credit card account by 5,000 dollars.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I dispute that amount of excess in lieu of why I had to default, but Citibank does not care, nor does the debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "The amount of the debt reverted to what it was at the time of the default, you can bet citibank would be working hard to work with me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1148", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Please consider robo-calls when developing rules for this section.", "reasons": ["2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "See my comments about robo-callers leaving messages on cell phones under robo-calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I understand the need to protect privacy,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but this is not the answer.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The messages left for me on my cell phone could have been returned by anyone with access to the cell phone (family members, snoopy friends) and information on a supposedly late payment would be disclosed by the robo-caller.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Robo-calling does not have the consumer's privacy in mind.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "732", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Massachusetts has this right.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "There need to be strict and enforceable limits on the number of times a collector can call during the week.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've received as many as 40 calls over a 5-day period from Citicards and calls every 50 minutes at work during the day by Wells Fargo.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "THIS IS SHAMEFUL", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "AND THIS FREQUENT REPEAT CALLING HAS TO BE STOPPED BY LAW!", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Those of us who are in debt know it and don't have to be reminded over and over again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Calling numerous times per day or per week won't get the debt paid any faster.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "If you explain that to the collector on the other end of the phone, they blame the repeat dialing on their computers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Now that's lame.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "The computers can be programmed to call once a day or a hundred times a day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Once is enough.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "306", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a creditor collecting my own debt, I assert that by the time I move to litgation, I've exhausted all other forms of collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've talked to, emailed, and snail mailed the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've tried to negotiate a payment plan or settlement offer all to no avail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Litigation is our last attempt.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Once we are litigation, we present our best case and let the debtor present their defense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "My experience is that debtors don't participate in their defense out of either fear or lack of knowledge about the legal process.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "But the burden of educating the debtor shouldn't be put on the creditor's shoulders.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "If debtor's prefer to ignore the issue, then a default judgment is justified.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be consequences to the inaction of the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "753", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been falsely subserved twice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Both times resulted in verdicts against me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Thank you for taking the time to express your viewpoint, which should carry a LOT OF WEIGHT", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "since you are in it at the ground level.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If I had not been falsely subserved, it is possible that the debt collector would have been more humbled and more amenable to my extremely generous offer of agreeing to the pay the debt in full based on what it was at the time of the default, as long as I could start with a very low monthly payment and build it up over time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "And as along as I was honoring my word, the debt would no longer be reported negatively on my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "But I never got that far", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "because the debt collection companies simply hired someone who would deliver a service, no questions asked as to its legality.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "332", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "I don't know if technology allows collectors to distinguish land lines from cell phones.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is fair for collectors to use info provided on the application for credit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should be allowed to assume that the mailing address of record is an accurate indication of the debtor's time zone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Creditors periodically request updates of contact info in some cases;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "this would be a good idea for all to do.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Mailing address should take priority for determining time zone unless the debtor advises otherwise.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "As mentioned previously, people with cell phones may move from one locale to another without changing their area code.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "764", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As I frequent many of the consumer credit forums,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I will tell you that most consumers do think that a debt can still be brought to court when the receive contact past the SOL.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "And others I have run into also still get contacted even after the 7 year mark when the debt has finally dropped from their credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "In fact, just the debt dropping off from the reports that has otherwise been dormant will get an automatic response from debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It seems they purposely wait for it to drop off and then pounce to instill fear. As in a \"gentle\" reminder that they are still there.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "They act like sharks in the water circling their prey.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "And the consumers bring up questions like \"when will this end?\" and \"I thought the debt wipes out after 7 years, why are they still contacting me?\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Something needs to be done about this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "SOL are SOL for a reason.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt collectors should not be able to harass and harass and harass.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "223", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Suspend further action to collect or re-sell.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Placing a rule that prohibits a collector from reporting information to a CRA during the 30 day window would be a nightmare from elm street and only cause more problems.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Unresolved disputes should not be sold and should be removed from collection..Period.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1134", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "just the phone number should show up on the called ID.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The consumer can google the number and figure out if they want to talk or call back the number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "More importantly, it gives attorneys the ability to make fdcpa claims against collection agencies", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "since we know who is calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "534", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I need a number to show.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Stop blocking yhr number and stop using 800 numbers.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "To me 800 numbers belong to sales or solicitors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I want to know I have a debt in collections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "So dont hide.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1113", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "paythefiddler, It's not just innocent family members that debt collectors go after, it's also perfect strangers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["1_4"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a common last name, no debts, and have been the target of many debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "All of the deadbeats have had my common last name and first initial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Once a debt collector has me on their hit list, they don't stop calling until I sent them a cease-communication letter.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "They want me to pay the debt to get them to stop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "639", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "With a fully communicative voicemail identifying the purpose of the call I think one call is quite diligent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If they choose to call and leave no message then they might as well have done nothing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "At least this way their message is being delivered.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1083", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I do think a \"free to end user\" would work ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and I don't see any problems with using such a practice or service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It creates some fairness for the collection companies and will not charge the cell owner if they do not have unlimited calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "364", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "It has been my experience that practices can vary greatly between various creditors who find it necessary to turn delinquent or defaulted debt over to a collection agnency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In my situation, little or no notification was given.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "At a minimum, a creditor should give specific information as to date and which company the debt is being assigned or sold to.", "reasons": ["3", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Getting such a notice would help me understand that there is going to be a change with whom I would be communicating with going forward.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The costs and expenses or problems that dad honors are collectors would have been giving those is miniscule compared to the problems cause by not giving notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I would argue that they would actually save money in the long run like giving such notices.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "At a minimum, The information that should be clear that in the notice is (1) the date of when the debt would be turned over to collection agency; (2) the name address of the collection constant company to whom the doubt was assigned; and (3) specific formation about the debt collection company and a list of that company's \"best practices\", policies and procedures as to what the consumer can expect.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It would be good if there could be a single-point-of-contact for this company as well as the supervisors and owner of the collection company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection agencies need to be forced to deal more forthrightly with consumers and be required to deal with greater transparency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "448", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't believe in abusive behavior ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "(i.e. the behavior spelled out in the FDCPA),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "but what this individual is saying that she owes a debt that she is not paying.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Instead, she wants to be the offensive party and paint the collector into a corner using a recording device.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "799", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Why should the consumer pay a filing fee at all if the collector is at fault?", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "That could be a hardship on many people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The collection agencies need to follow the rules of doing their validation correctly,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and this would not be an issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1330", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection agencies are not an all loose for the consumer nor they should be.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Some collections agencies have gone beyond their job scope and their role in the process of repayment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "974", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "While Demand Letters can be ineffective for the purpose of collecting a debt, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "\"notice is the hallmark of fairness.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It's more important that people are held to standards, ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "which, in turn, help to eliminate abusive practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Procedural safeguards, like demand letters, are an important standard regardless of their effectiveness.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1311", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "In my opinion,collection companies,credit bureaus, and every one in between should be made to have some type of soft ware that could identify time-barred debt.Plus, regulation that will not allow creditors/buyers to reactivate an old debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If a given state has its own statue of limitation regarding a legitimate time line to collect a debt, so be it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The Validation Notice,should identify the true facts of the debt in question.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "After complete due process has been exhausted, the record should be completely removed from the consumer file.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "377", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a common last name, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and for about three years I was bombarded with collection calls for other individuals with my last name and first initial.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I finally changed my phone listing from my initials to my nickname and have had only collection call since.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am an elderly retiree.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have no car loan or mortgage.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I pay all my bills on time, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I don't carry balances on my credit cards.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "No debt collector has ever admitted to me that they got my number out of the phone but, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "but that's what they're doing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to see every debt collector tell the individual they are calling the source of their information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "I now have a long list of people with debts in collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "Since I'm not a debt collector,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "I don't believe that I have a legal obligation not to reveal their names.", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "I do, however, believe that I have a moral obligation not to do so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "Please find a way to keep debt collectors from harassing innocent people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "452", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have worked in collections for 13 years with mostly first parties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "All of these institutions have complied with the FDCPA and seek to service their lost members to the best of their abilities.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "467", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been harassed for years (after getting a new cell phone number) from debt collectors calling for someone else.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I presume it is the person who had my phone number before me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "No matter how many times I tell them that they have the wrong number, they just keep calling over and over.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1033", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "It's important to understand that a Validation Notice (sent within 5 days pursuant to 1692g) is NOT a validation of debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "It's a NOTICE of your right to validation, if you choose to invoke it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "I do agree that there should be additional regulation around this issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But part of the problem is the way the statute is written.", "reasons": ["4_5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Most collectors cite 1692g verbatim to avoid liability for misleading consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "But it's kind of a big convoluted sentence that the average person can't understand.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "I'd like to see a plain language amendment to that section of the FDCPA,", "reasons": ["3", "5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1398", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is the PROBLEM over and over", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Why should lawyers get a pass from rules of the Bar Associations or rules of the court because they are now considered \"debt collectors\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "even I did not know this, though I have seen advertised quite a bit lawyers in the \"collection\" business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This is wrong.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I hope if anything, this very thing is addressed.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Using a lawyer to send a letter is often a way to intimidate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "People become too frightened to even respond.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "The rules are blown off by lawyers who go into this debt collection business ", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "because they make a fast easy buck, and they know the debtor has very little recourse, and there is so few rules that protect the consumer/debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "Being in debt stopped being a crime decades ago,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "but the lack of rules that protect the debtor are bringing back these draconian practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "Uniformity, is needed, and making lawyers abide by the rules of the Bar.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "It is bringing to light why this system has become so fraught with abuse.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "638", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Like most regulatory programs additional cost would be inevitable,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "it could be paid for by a yearly fee that collectors pay to be a licensed collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "466", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am concerned that state and federal agencies are contributing to identity theft, big time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "In just the past month I had to make an online payment on what I believe was a federal hobbs act violation by the Los Angeles building and Safety department.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "A day after making the payment or risk losing my home, that same credit card was being used online by thieves.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Then a few weeks later another agency asked for bank documents, I supplied them via fax, and they were lost!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "And on top of that, there really didn't seem to be a big deal made out of the fact that the documents went missing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
